<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;leping </eesti>
<inglise>Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;leping on t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja kokkulepe, mille kohaselt t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustub tegema t&ouml;&ouml;andjale t&ouml;&ouml;d, alludes tema juhtimisele ja kontrollile, t&ouml;&ouml;andja aga kohustub maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml; eest tasu ning kindlustama talle poolte kokkuleppe, kollektiivlepingu, seaduse v&otilde;i haldusaktiga etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>An employment contract is an agreement between an employee and an employer under which the employee undertakes to do work for the employer in subordination to the management and supervision of the employer, and the employer undertakes to remunerate the employee for such work and to provide the working conditions prescribed in the agreement between the parties, a collective agreement, law or administrative legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja </eesti>
<inglise>Employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajaks v&otilde;ib olla 18-aastaseks saanud teov&otilde;imeline v&otilde;i piiratult teov&otilde;imeline f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A natural person who has attained eighteen years of age and has active legal capacity or restricted active legal capacity may be an employee. </inglise>
<eesti>Seadusega v&otilde;ib m&otilde;ne kategooria t&ouml;&ouml;tajate jaoks kehtestada k&otilde;rgendatud vanusem&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise>A higher age limit may be established by law for certain categories of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Erandjuhtudel v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tajaks olla: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In exceptional cases, an employee may be: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 15-aastaseks saanud alaealine - &uuml;he vanema v&otilde;i hooldaja kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tamine ei ohusta alaealise tervist, k&otilde;lblust ja hariduse omandamist ega ole alaealistele keelatud seaduse v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a minor who has attained fifteen years of age, with the written consent of one parent or a curator, if the work does not endanger the health, morality or education of the minor and is not prohibited to minors by law or a collective agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 13 - 15-aastane alaealine - &uuml;he vanema v&otilde;i eestkostja ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul ning vabariigi valitsuse poolt kinnitatud nimekirjas loetletud t&ouml;&ouml;del, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tamine ei ohusta alaealise tervist, k&otilde;lblust ja hariduse omandamist ega ole alaealistele keelatud kollektiivlepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a minor of thirteen to fifteen years of age, with the written consent of one parent or a guardian and the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer, for work set out in a list approved by the Government of the Republic, if the work does not endanger the health, morality or education of the minor and is not prohibited to minors by a collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja </eesti>
<inglise>Employer </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andjaks v&otilde;ib olla: </eesti>
<inglise>The following may be an employer: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juriidiline isik; </eesti>
<inglise>1) legal persons; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juriidilise isiku struktuuri&uuml;ksus, kui talle on antud t&ouml;&ouml;andja &otilde;igused; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a structural unit of a legal person if it has been granted the rights of an employer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teov&otilde;imeline f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a natural person with active legal capacity. </inglise>
<eesti>Seadusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel peab t&ouml;&ouml;andja olema vanem kui 18-aastane. </eesti>
<inglise>In the cases prescribed by law, an employer must be older than eighteen years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Varem s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtivus </eesti>
<inglise>Validity of employment contracts entered into previously </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;leping, mis s&otilde;lmiti enne t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja jaoks k&otilde;rgendatud vanusem&auml;&auml;ra kehtima hakkamist (paragrahv 2 l&otilde;ige 1 ja paragrahv 3 punkt 3), j&auml;&auml;b j&otilde;usse ka niisuguse vanusem&auml;&auml;ra kehtima hakkamisel, kui seadus ei n&auml;e ette teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>An employment contract that is entered into before a higher age limit for an employee or employer enters into force (subsection (2) 1) and clause 3 3)) remains in force when such age limit enters into force, unless otherwise prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse rakendusala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Employment Contracts Act </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seadus laieneb k&otilde;igile t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjatele, kes s&otilde;lmisid t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu. </eesti>
<inglise>The Employment Contracts Act extends to all employees and employers who enter into employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettev&otilde;te s&otilde;lmib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu ka oma liikme, osaniku v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;riga, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab samas ettev&otilde;ttes. </eesti>
<inglise>Enterprises enter into employment contracts with their members, shareholders or stockholders who work in the enterprises. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtivus ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni reorganiseerimisel, alluvuse, omaniku v&otilde;i omandivormi muutumisel v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte &uuml;leminekul </eesti>
<inglise>Validity of employment contracts upon reorganisation or change of subordination, ownership or form of ownership of enterprise, agency or other organisation, and upon transfer of enterprise </inglise>
<eesti>Ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni reorganiseerimine, alluvuse, omaniku v&otilde;i omandivormi muutumine v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte &uuml;leminek ei l&otilde;peta t&ouml;&ouml;lepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>The reorganisation or change of subordination, ownership or form of ownership of an enterprise, agency or other organisation or the transfer of an enterprise does not terminate employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtumid, millele t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seadus ei laiene </eesti>
<inglise>Circumstances to which Employment Contracts Act does not extend </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seadus ei laiene: </eesti>
<inglise>The Employment Contracts Act does not extend to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teenistusele Riigikogu liikmena, Vabariigi Presidendina v&otilde;i Riigikogu v&otilde;i Vabariigi Presidendi poolt ametisse nimetatava ametnikuna; </eesti>
<inglise>1) service as a member of the Riigikogu (2), the President of the Republic or an official appointed to office by the President of the Republic or the Riigikogu; </inglise>
<eesti>2) riigiametnikele ja kohaliku omavalitsuse ametnikele, kelle teenistussuhteid reguleeritakse avaliku teenistuse seadusega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) state officials and local government officials whose service relationships are regulated by the Public Service Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kaitsej&otilde;udude tegevteenistusele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) active service in the armed forces; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;tamisele taluperes v&otilde;i pereettev&otilde;ttes talupere v&otilde;i pereettev&otilde;tte liikmena; </eesti>
<inglise>4) work as a member of a farm family for family enterprise in a family farm enterprise or family enterprise; </inglise>
<eesti>5) vanemate, abikaasade ja laste t&ouml;&ouml;tamisele &uuml;ksteise koduses majapidamises, samuti mainitud isikute poolt &uuml;ksteise eest hoolitsemisele; </eesti>
<inglise>5) household work by parents, spouses or children for one another and care by such persons for one another; </inglise>
<eesti>6) perekonnaliikmete t&ouml;&ouml;tamisele &uuml;hises koduses majapidamises, samuti perekonnaliikme eest hoolitsemisele; </eesti>
<inglise>6) work by family members in a shared household and care for family members; </inglise>
<eesti>7) t&ouml;&ouml;tamisele teenistuslepingu alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>7) work on the basis of a contract of service. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuslepingut reguleerib eriseadus; </eesti>
<inglise>Contracts of service are regulated by a specific Act. </inglise>
<eesti>8) t&ouml;&ouml;tamisele usuorganisatsioonis kultusetoiminguid sooritava isikuna, kui mainitud organisatsiooni p&otilde;hidokument ei n&otilde;ua niisuguse isikuga t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimist; </eesti>
<inglise>8) work in a religious organisation as a person conducting religious services if the fundamental document of such organisation does not require entry into an employment contract with such person; </inglise>
<eesti>9) volituse alusel tehingute t&auml;itmisele, kui niisugust tehingut t&auml;itev isik saab tehingult tulu ja tal lasub varaline riisiko tehingu &otilde;nnestumise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>9) performance of a transaction on the basis of an authorisation if the person performing such transaction receives income from the transaction and bears proprietary risk for the success of the transaction; </inglise>
<eesti>10) juriidilise isiku organi ja v&auml;lismaa &auml;ri&uuml;hingu Eesti filiaali juhataja, samuti riigiettev&otilde;tte haldusn&otilde;ukogu liikme suhetele juriidilise isiku, v&auml;lismaa &auml;ri&uuml;hingu Eesti filiaali ja riigiettev&otilde;ttega; </eesti>
<inglise>10) relationships of directors of bodies of legal persons or Estonian branches of foreign companies, and members of administrative boards of state enterprises with legal persons, Estonian branches of foreign companies or state enterprises. </inglise>
<eesti>(28.05.96 j&otilde;ust.08.06.96 - RT I 1996, 40, 773) </eesti>
<inglise>(28.05.96 entered into force 08.06.96 - RT I 1996, 40, 773) </inglise>
<eesti>11) tegutsemisele t&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tulepingu v&otilde;i muu tsiviil&otilde;igusliku lepingu alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>11) activities based on contracts for services or other civil law contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>12) t&ouml;&ouml;tamisele vabadusekaotuse kandmise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>12) work performed during imprisonment. </inglise>
<eesti>Vabadusekaotuseta paranduslikke t&ouml;id tegevatele isikutele laieneb t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seadus teiste seadustega etten&auml;htud erisustega; </eesti>
<inglise>The Employment Contracts Act extends to persons who do community work in lieu of imprisonment, subject to the exceptions prescribed by other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>13) seaduses otseselt etten&auml;htud muule tegevusele, samuti seaduses otseselt mainitud isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>13) other activities directly prescribed by law and persons directly referred to by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.01.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 16, 228) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.01.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 16, 228) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidlus lepingu olemuse &uuml;le </eesti>
<inglise>Dispute over nature of contract </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluse korral lepingu olemuse &uuml;le loetakse, et pooled s&otilde;lmisid t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu, kui v&auml;idetav t&ouml;&ouml;andja ei t&otilde;enda vastupidist v&otilde;i kui pole ilmne, et pooled s&otilde;lmisid teistsuguse lepingu. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of a dispute over the nature of a contract, the parties are deemed to have entered into an employment contract unless the alleged employer proves otherwise or unless it is evident that the parties entered into a different kind of contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Varjatud tehing </eesti>
<inglise>Concealed transaction </inglise>
<eesti>Kui pooled s&otilde;lmisid t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu teise tehingu varjamiseks, kohaldatakse selle tehingu kohta k&auml;ivaid s&auml;tteid, mida pooled tegelikult silmas pidasid. </eesti>
<inglise>If the parties enter into an employment contract in order to conceal another transaction, the provisions pertaining to the transaction which the parties actually intended apply. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Seadusevastane eelistamine ja &otilde;iguste piiramine </eesti>
<inglise>Illegal preferences and restriction of rights </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seadusevastane on eeliste lubamine ja andmine ning &otilde;iguste piiramine s&otilde;ltuvalt t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja soost, rahvusest, nahav&auml;rvist, rassist, emakeelest, sotsiaalsest p&auml;ritolust, &uuml;hiskondlikust seisundist, varasemast tegevusest, usulistest, poliitilistest v&otilde;i muudest veendumustest ja suhtest kaitseteenistuse kohustusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) It is illegal to allow or give preferences, or to restrict rights on the grounds of the sex, nationality, colour, race, native language, social origin, social status, previous activities, religion, political or other opinion, or attitude towards the duty to serve in the armed forces of employees or employers. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti on seadusevastane t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja &otilde;iguste piiramine s&otilde;ltuvalt perekonnaseisust, perekondlikest kohustustest, kuuluvusest kodanike &uuml;hendustesse ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjate huvide esindamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>It is also illegal to restrict the rights of employees or employers on the grounds of marital status, family obligations, membership in citizens' associations, or representation of the interests of employees or employers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikega ei ole vastuolus: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is not contrary to subsection (1) of this section to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) eeliste lubamine ja andmine seoses raseduse v&otilde;i laste kasvatamisega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) allow and give preferences based on pregnancy or the raising of children; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tmisel ja t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete andmisel t&ouml;&ouml;taja soo arvesse v&otilde;tmine, kui see on m&ouml;&ouml;dap&auml;&auml;smatu t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomu v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) take into account the sex of an employee in hiring or assigning duties if this is unavoidable due to the nature of the work or working conditions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajale usuliste vajaduste rahuldamiseks sobiva t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeajare&zcaron;iimi v&otilde;imaldamine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) allow a suitable working and rest time regime which satisfies the religious requirements of an employee; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;ks vajaliku keelteoskuse n&otilde;udmine ja keelte valdamise eest h&uuml;vede andmine. </eesti>
<inglise>4) require language skills necessary for the work and pay compensation for proficiency in languages. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsi kasvatavate isikute soodustused </eesti>
<inglise>Benefits for persons raising children </inglise>
<eesti>Soodustused, mis on paragrahvi 51 2. l&otilde;ikes, paragrahvi 63 2. l&otilde;ikes, paragrahvis 67, paragrahvi 79 2. l&otilde;ikes ja paragrahvis 92 ette n&auml;htud naisele, kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla kolmeaastast last, laienevad ka: </eesti>
<inglise>The benefits prescribed in subsections 51 (2) and 63 (2), &sect; 67, subsection 79 (2) and &sect; 92 for women raising disabled children or children under three years of age also extend to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikule, kes ilma emata kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla kolmeaastast last; </eesti>
<inglise>1) persons raising motherless children who are disabled or under three years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alla kolmeaastase lapse eestkostjale; </eesti>
<inglise>2) guardians of children who are under three years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lapsinvaliidi eestkostjale v&otilde;i hooldajale. </eesti>
<inglise>3) guardians or curators of disabled children. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Alaealised </eesti>
<inglise>Minors </inglise>
<eesti>Alaealistel on t&ouml;&ouml;suhetes ja t&ouml;&ouml;vaidlustes v&otilde;rdsed &otilde;igused t&auml;isealistega ning seaduse, haldusakti ja kollektiivlepinguga etten&auml;htud soodustused. </eesti>
<inglise>Minors enjoy equal rights with adults in employment relationships and disputes, and they have benefits prescribed by law, administrative legislation and collective agreements. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisriigi kodanikud ja kodakondsuseta isikud </eesti>
<inglise>Citizens of foreign states and stateless persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eestis alaliselt elavatel v&auml;lisriigi kodanikel ja kodakondsuseta isikutel on Eesti kodanikega v&otilde;rdsed t&ouml;&ouml;alased &otilde;igused, kui seadus ei n&auml;e ette teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Citizens of foreign states and stateless persons who reside in Estonia permanently have rights pertaining to employment equal to those of Estonian citizens unless otherwise prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eestis ajutiselt v&otilde;i t&auml;htajaliselt elavate v&auml;lisriigi kodanike ja kodakondsuseta isikute t&ouml;&ouml;alased eritingimused n&auml;hakse ette seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Specific conditions pertaining to employment of citizens of foreign states and stateless persons who are residing in Estonia temporarily or for a specified period of time shall be prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja &otilde;iguste laiendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Extension of employees' rights </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale seaduse v&otilde;i haldusaktiga antud &otilde;igusi v&otilde;ib laiendada kollektiiv- ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolse otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The rights granted to employees by law or administrative legislation may be extended by collective agreements or employment contracts, or by unilateral decisions of employers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale kollektiivlepinguga antud &otilde;igusi v&otilde;ib laiendada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolse otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rights granted to employees by collective agreements may be extended by employment contracts or unilateral decisions of employers. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja olukorda halvendavate t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu tingimuste kehtetus </eesti>
<inglise>Invalidity of employment contract terms which are unfavourable to employees </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu tingimused, mis on t&ouml;&ouml;taja jaoks halvemad seaduses, haldusaktis v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingus ette n&auml;htust, on kehtetud. </eesti>
<inglise>Employment contract terms which are less favourable to employees than those prescribed by law, administrative legislation or a collective agreement are invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui pooled ei lepi kokku uutes tingimustes, kohaldatakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetute tingimuste asemel seadust, haldusakti v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>The law, administrative legislation or collective agreement applies instead of the invalid employment contract terms unless the parties agree on new terms. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja olukorda halvendavate t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolsete otsuste kehtetus </eesti>
<inglise>Invalidity of unilateral decisions of employers which are unfavourable to employees </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolse otsusega kehtestatud tingimused, mis on t&ouml;&ouml;taja jaoks halvemad seaduses, haldusaktis, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htust, on kehtetud. </eesti>
<inglise>Terms established by unilateral decisions of employers which are less favourable to employees than those prescribed by law, administrative legislation, collective agreements or employment contracts are invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>Kehtetute tingimuste asemel kohaldatakse seadust, haldusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>The law, administrative legislation, collective agreement or employment contract applies instead of the invalid terms. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja jaoks soodsaima s&auml;tte kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of provisions which are more favourable to employees </inglise>
<eesti>S&auml;tete vastuolu korral kohaldatakse s&auml;tet, mis on t&ouml;&ouml;taja jaoks soodsaim. </eesti>
<inglise>In the event of a conflict between provisions, the provision which is more favourable to employees applies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hepoolsed toimingud </eesti>
<inglise>Unilateral actions </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu &uuml;hepoolne muutmine, peatamine, l&otilde;petamine ja t&uuml;histamine on lubatud ainult seaduses, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The unilateral amendment, suspension, termination or cancellation of an employment contract is permitted only under the conditions and pursuant to the procedures provided by law, a collective agreement or the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Pidev t&ouml;&ouml;staa&zcaron; sama t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures </eesti>
<inglise>Continuous length of employment with same employer </inglise>
<eesti>Pidevat t&ouml;&ouml;staa&zcaron;i sama t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures arvutatakse eeskirjade j&auml;rgi, mis on kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt v&otilde;i kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>Continuous length of employment with the same employer is calculated in accordance with the rules established by the employer, in a collective agreement or the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Igal juhul arvatakse mainitud staa&zcaron;i hulka sama t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel vaheaegadeta t&ouml;&ouml;tatud aeg, t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise aeg ja sunnitult t&ouml;&ouml;lt puudutud aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>In each case, time worked without breaks, time during which the employment contract is suspended and time of compelled absence from work is included in the length of employment with the same employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;raamat </eesti>
<inglise>Employment record book </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;raamat on t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tamist t&otilde;endav p&otilde;hidokument. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment record book is a fundamental document proving employment under an employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud pidama t&ouml;&ouml;raamatut k&otilde;igi p&otilde;hikohaga t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employers are required to maintain employment record books for all employees who are employed in a principal job. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse kantakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following is entered in an employment record book: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;taja ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the given name and surname of the employee; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;nniaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date of birth of the employee; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg, sealhulgas erikandega t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg t&ouml;&ouml;del v&otilde;i tingimustes, mis annavad t&ouml;&ouml;tajale &otilde;iguse soodustuspensionile v&otilde;i pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i soodustatud korras arvutamisele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the duration of employment under the employment contract, including special entries concerning the duration of employment or conditions which grant the employee the right to pension benefits or calculation of pensionable age under favoured conditions; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumine paragrahvi 55 punktide 1-2 ja 7 alusel kauemaks kui kolmeks kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a suspension of the employment contract pursuant to clauses 55 1), 2) and 7) for more than three months. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;udel kantakse t&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) At the request of an employee, the following is entered in his or her employment record book: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamise aluse formuleering viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a statement of the basis for termination or declaration of invalidity of the employment contract with reference to the section, subsection and clause of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) andmed tehtud t&ouml;&ouml;de ja t&auml;idetud ametikohtade kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) information relating to the work performed and the offices held; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kohakaasluse korras t&ouml;&ouml;tatud aeg, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja esitab p&otilde;hikoha t&ouml;&ouml;andjale dokumendi, mis t&otilde;endab kohakaasluse korras t&ouml;&ouml;tamist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the duration of employment in a second job if the employee presents a document to the employer in the principal job proving employment in the second job; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures paragrahvide 67 ja 68 alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tatud aeg, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja esitab p&otilde;hikoha t&ouml;&ouml;andjale niisugust t&ouml;&ouml;tamist t&otilde;endava dokumendi. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the duration of employment at the workplace of another employer pursuant to &sect;&sect; 67 and 68 if the employee presents a document to the employer in the principal job proving such employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Andmeid, mida ei ole k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. ja 4. l&otilde;ikes mainitud, t&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse ei kanta. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Information which is not referred to in subsections (3) and (4) of this section is not entered in an employment record book. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;raamatu vormi, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu t&auml;itmise ja dublikaadi andmise korra ning t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu hinna kehtestab Sotsiaalministeerium. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Ministry of Social Affairs shall establish the format, procedure for completion and issue of duplicates, and the price of employment record books. </inglise>
<eesti>(26.06.96 j&otilde;ust.26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </eesti>
<inglise>(26.06.96 entered into force 26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajate arvestus ja dokumentide s&auml;ilitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of employees and preservation of documents </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja peab arvestust k&otilde;igi t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kohta isikukaartidel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers shall maintain records on all employees in personnel files. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajate arvestuse korra ja isikukaardile kantavate andmete loetelu kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for maintaining records and the list of information to be entered in personnel files shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingut, isikukaarti ning v&auml;lja v&otilde;tmata t&ouml;&ouml;raamatut s&auml;ilitatakse 50 aastat, arvates t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The employment contract, the personnel file, and the employment record book if it is left with the employer shall be preserved for fifty years as of the termination of the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevuse l&otilde;petamisel annab t&ouml;&ouml;andja nimetatud dokumendid &uuml;le arhiiviasutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>If the activities of the employer are terminated, the employer shall transfer the specified documents to an archival agency. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i selle organisatsiooniliselt iseseisva osa &uuml;leminekul annab t&ouml;&ouml;andja dokumendid &uuml;le enda &otilde;igusj&auml;rglasele. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the transfer of the enterprise or organisationally independent part thereof, the employer shall transfer the documents to the legal successor of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 669) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.12.2000 entered into force 07.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 669) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale &otilde;iendite ja iseloomustuse andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of certificates and assessments to employees </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja on t&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;udel kohustatud andma talle: </eesti>
<inglise>At the request of an employee, the employer is required to provide the employee with: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kalendriaasta l&otilde;pul, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel &otilde;iendi makstud palga, kinnipeetud &uuml;ksikisiku tulumaksu ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja kasuks tehtud kindlustusmaksete kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>1) a certificate of paid wages, personal income tax deductions and insurance payments made for the benefit of the employee, at the end of each calendar year and upon the termination of the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iendi vormi kehtestab Maksuamet; </eesti>
<inglise>The format of the certificate shall be established by the Tax Board; </inglise>
<eesti>(26.06.96 j&otilde;ust.26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </eesti>
<inglise>(26.06.96 entered into force 26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;iendi, milles n&auml;idatakse, kellena ja kui kaua t&ouml;&ouml;taja on selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures t&ouml;&ouml;tanud. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a certificate showing in what capacity and for what length the employee has worked for the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;udel kantakse &otilde;iendisse ka t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamise aluse formuleering viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile; </eesti>
<inglise>At the request of the employee, a statement of the basis for termination or declaration of invalidity of the employment contract with reference to the section, subsection and clause of this Act shall be entered in the certificate; </inglise>
<eesti>3) iseloomustuse. </eesti>
<inglise>3) references. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektori otsuse tegemise t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Time limits for decisions of labour inspectors </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seadusega etten&auml;htud otsused teeb t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor kahe n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates tema poole p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>Labour inspectors shall render decisions prescribed in this Act within two weeks after the date on which they are consulted. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Erieeskirjade kehtestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of special rules </inglise>
<eesti>Seadusega v&otilde;ib m&otilde;ne kategooria t&ouml;&ouml;tajate, samuti m&otilde;ne kategooria t&ouml;&ouml;andjate jaoks kehtestada teistsugused eeskirjad kui need, mis sisalduvad k&auml;esolevas seaduses. </eesti>
<inglise>Rules which differ from those contained in this Act may be established by law for certain categories of employees and certain categories of employers. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahvusvaheline leping </eesti>
<inglise>International agreements </inglise>
<eesti>Kui seadus, haldusakt, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;leping v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolne otsus on vastuolus Eestile kohustusliku rahvusvahelise lepinguga, mis n&auml;eb selgelt ja &uuml;hem&otilde;tteliselt ette, et lepingut kohaldatakse, s&otilde;ltumata siseriikliku seaduse v&otilde;i haldusakti vastuv&otilde;tmisest, kohaldatakse rahvusvahelist lepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>If an Act, administrative legislation, collective agreement, employment contract or unilateral decision of an employer is contrary to an international agreement binding on Estonia which expressly and unambiguously prescribes application of the agreement notwithstanding the passage of national law or administrative legislation, the international agreement applies. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimine </eesti>
<inglise>Entry into Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kohustuslikud tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Mandatory provisions of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kohustuslikeks tingimusteks on j&auml;rgnevad kokkulepped: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following are mandatory provisions of employment contracts: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tehtava t&ouml;&ouml;, selle keerukusastme, ameti- v&otilde;i kutsenimetuse ja kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the work to be performed and its level of complexity, its official or professional title, and the qualification requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;aja kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the working time; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tasu kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the wages; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml; tegemise asukoha kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the location of employment; </inglise>
<eesti>5) m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtivusaja kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the term of validity of an employment contract for a specified term; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&ouml;&ouml;le asumise aja kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the date of commencement of employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu tingimusteks v&otilde;ivad olla ka kokkulepped muudes k&uuml;simustes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Agreements on other issues may be included as provisions in employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment contract is entered into for: </inglise>
<eesti>1) m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an unspecified term; </inglise>
<eesti>2) m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks kas lepingut&auml;htaja kalendaarse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramisega v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; l&otilde;ppemisega, kuid mitte kauemaks kui viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a specified term, whether the term of a contract is fixed by a specific date or by completion of the work, but for not longer than five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmida: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employment contract may be entered into for a specified term: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teatud t&ouml;&ouml; tegemise ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for completion of a specific task; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ajutiselt &auml;raoleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja asendamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for replacement of an employee who is temporarily absent; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;de mahu ajutisel suurenemisel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) for a temporary increase in work volume; </inglise>
<eesti>4) hooajat&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) for performance of seasonal work; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kui t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus n&auml;hakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ette erisoodustused (v&auml;lja&otilde;pe t&ouml;&ouml;andja kulul, t&ouml;&ouml;andja loobumine t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest t&ouml;&ouml;taja koondamise t&otilde;ttu jms.); </eesti>
<inglise>5) if the employment contract prescribes special benefits (training at the expense of the employer, waiver by the employer of termination of the employment contract due to a lay-off of the employee etc.); </inglise>
<eesti>6) seadusega, samuti vabariigi valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rustega etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>6) in the cases prescribed by law or by regulations of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&auml;htaeg on m&auml;rkimata, loetakse t&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmituks m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the term of an employment contract is not specified, the employment contract is deemed to have been entered into for an unspecified term. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu vorm </eesti>
<inglise>Format of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmitakse kahes eksemplaris, millest &uuml;ks j&auml;&auml;b t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, teine t&ouml;&ouml;andjale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment contract is entered into in duplicate original copies of which one copy is retained by the employee and the other with the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>Ainult t&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks, mille kestus ei &uuml;leta kaht n&auml;dalat, v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmida suuliselt. </eesti>
<inglise>An oral employment contract may be entered into only for employment for a term of less than two weeks. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegelikult t&ouml;&ouml;le lubamine t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt on v&otilde;rdsustatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimisega, s&otilde;ltumata t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu vormistamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Permitting an employee to commence work is equivalent to entering into an employment contract, regardless of whether the employment contract has been formalised. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul vormistatakse t&ouml;&ouml;leping kirjalikult tingimustel, mida tegelikult kohaldati. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the employment contract is formalised in writing with the terms which actually applied. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tegelikud tingimused olid t&ouml;&ouml;taja jaoks halvemad seaduses, haldusaktis v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingus etten&auml;htust, kohaldatakse vastavat seadust, haldusakti v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>If the actual terms were less favourable to the employee than those prescribed by law, administrative legislation or collective agreement, then the appropriate law, administrative legislation or collective agreement applies. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu vormistamata j&auml;tmine v&otilde;i n&otilde;uetevastase vormistamise eest kannab t&ouml;&ouml;andja haldusvastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Employers bear administrative liability for failure to formalise or for unsatisfactory formalisation of employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimine isiklikult </eesti>
<inglise>Entry into employment contract in person </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmib t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja selleks volitatud esindajaga iga t&ouml;&ouml;taja, ka alaealine, isiklikult. </eesti>
<inglise>All employees, including minors, enter into employment contracts with employers or the authorised representatives of employers in person. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;leping loetakse s&otilde;lmituks, kui pooled on lepingule alla kirjutanud v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja on t&ouml;&ouml;le lubatud. </eesti>
<inglise>An employment contract is deemed to have been entered into when the parties have signed the contract or the employee commences work. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimiseks n&otilde;utavad dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Documents required for entry into employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimiseks n&otilde;uab t&ouml;&ouml;andja j&auml;rgmiste dokumentide esitamist: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to enter into an employment contract, an employer requires presentation of the following documents: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikut t&otilde;endav dokument; </eesti>
<inglise>1) identification; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;raamat; </eesti>
<inglise>2) an employment record book; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tunnistus (diplom) vajaliku kvalifikatsiooni v&otilde;i hariduse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) certificate (diploma) regarding the necessary qualifications or education; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&otilde;end (sanitaarraamat) tervise kohta, kui t&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmitakse t&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks t&ouml;&ouml;l, kus on ette n&auml;htud eelnev ja perioodiline tervisekontroll, samuti alla 21-aastase isiku t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tmisel erieeskirjades etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;dele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) certificate (health record) regarding health if the employment contract is entered into for work where prior and periodic medical examinations are prescribed, or upon hiring persons who are under twenty-one years of age for work prescribed in special rules. </inglise>
<eesti>Niisuguste t&ouml;&ouml;de loetelu kinnitab vabariigi valitsus ja mainitud t&otilde;endi (sanitaarraamatu) vormi kinnitab tervishoiuministeerium; </eesti>
<inglise>The Government of the Republic shall approve the list of such work and the Ministry of Health shall approve the format of such certificates (health records). </inglise>
<eesti>5) &uuml;he vanema v&otilde;i eestkostja ja t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori kirjalik n&otilde;usolek 13- kuni 15-aastase alaealise t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the written consent of one parent or guardian and the labour inspector upon hiring a minor between thirteen and fifteen years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>6) &uuml;he vanema v&otilde;i hooldaja kirjalik n&otilde;usolek 15-aastaseks saanud alaealise t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the written consent of one parent or curator upon hiring a minor who has attained fifteen years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>7) seadusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel t&ouml;&ouml;tamisluba v&auml;lismaalase v&otilde;i kodakondsuseta isiku t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a work permit upon hiring an alien or stateless person in the cases prescribed by law; </inglise>
<eesti>8) muud dokumendid seaduse v&otilde;i vabariigi valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>8) other documents in the cases prescribed by law or regulations of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tmisel on keelatud n&otilde;uda dokumente, mida ei ole ette n&auml;htud seaduse v&otilde;i vabariigi valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon hiring, it is prohibited to require documents which are not prescribed by law or regulations of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus omaalgatuslikult esitada t&ouml;&ouml;andjale iseloomustusi, soovitusi ja muid dokumente, mis iseloomustavad tema eelnenud t&ouml;&ouml;tamist ning kutseoskuste olemasolu ja kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) On their own initiative, employees have the right to present employers with references, recommendations and other documents which characterise their previous work performance and the existence and application of their professional skills. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andjaks on f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud registreerima kirjaliku t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;leasumise p&auml;evast, oma elukoha t&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioonis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an employer is a natural person, the employer is required to register a written employment contract within one week after the date that an employee commences employment with the labour inspectorate of the employer's place of residence. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu registreerimata j&auml;tmine ei m&otilde;juta lepingu kehtivust. </eesti>
<inglise>Failure to register an employment contract does not affect the validity of the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu registreerimata j&auml;tmise eest kannab t&ouml;&ouml;andja haldusvastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employers bear administrative liability for failure to register employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Sugulaste ja h&otilde;imlaste koos t&ouml;&ouml;tamise piiramine </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on work with relatives and relatives by marriage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;hes ja samas riiklikus v&otilde;i munitsipaalettev&otilde;ttes, -asutuses v&otilde;i muus riiklikus v&otilde;i munitsipaalorganisatsioonis on keelatud omavahel l&auml;hedases suguluses (vanemad, vennad, &otilde;ed, lapsed) v&otilde;i h&otilde;imluses (abikaasa, abikaasa vanemad, vennad, &otilde;ed, lapsed) olevatel isikutel t&ouml;&ouml;tada &uuml;ksteise vahetus alluvuses olevatel v&otilde;i teise poolt vahetult kontrollitavatel ametikohtadel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) It is prohibited for persons who are close relatives (parents, brothers, sisters, children) or close relatives by marriage (a spouse, spouse's parents, brothers, sisters, children) to work in the same state or municipal enterprise, agency or other state or municipal organisation in positions which are directly subordinate to or have direct control over the other. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametikohtade loetelu, mille t&auml;itmisel ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikega etten&auml;htud piiranguid, kehtestatakse seaduse v&otilde;i vabariigi valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The list of positions which are not subject to the restrictions prescribed in subsection (1) of this section shall be established by law or a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Katseaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Probationary period </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingus kokkulepitud t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks t&ouml;&ouml;tajal vajaliku tervise, v&otilde;imete, suhtlemisalase sobivuse ja kutseoskuste kindlakstegemiseks v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus ette n&auml;ha katseaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment contract may prescribe a probationary period in order to confirm that the employee has the necessary health, abilities, suitable social skills and professional skills to perform the work agreed on in the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Katseaeg ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada nelja kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A probationary period shall not exceed four months. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Katseaja hulka ei arvata aega, mil t&ouml;&ouml;leping oli peatatud paragrahvi 55 punktide 1-6 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Time during which an employment contract is suspended pursuant to clauses 55 (1) -(6) is not included in a probationary period. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Katseajal on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal k&otilde;ik seadustest, haldusaktidest ning kollektiiv- ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingust tulenevad &otilde;igused ja kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) During a probationary period, an employee has the rights and duties provided by law, administrative legislation, a collective agreement and the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Katseaega ei rakendata: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A probationary period is not applied: </inglise>
<eesti>1) alaealistele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to minors; </inglise>
<eesti>2) invaliidide t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmisel neile etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;- (ameti-) kohtadele. </eesti>
<inglise>2) upon hiring disabled persons for employment (professional) positions which are prescribed for them. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Katseaja tulemused </eesti>
<inglise>Results of probationary period </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Katseaja tulemused m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks t&ouml;&ouml;andja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The results of probationary periods are determined by employers. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja ei ole rahul katseaja tulemustega, on tal &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petada (paragrahvi 86 punkt 5). </eesti>
<inglise>If an employer is not satisfied with the results of a probationary period, the employer has the right to terminate the employment contract (clause 86 5)). </inglise>
<eesti>Katseaja kestel on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petada. </eesti>
<inglise>During a probationary period, an employee has the right to terminate his or her employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui katseaeg on l&otilde;ppenud ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja j&auml;tkab t&ouml;&ouml;d, loetakse ta katse sooritanuks ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib temaga t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petada ainult teistel seaduses etten&auml;htud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a probationary period has ended and the employee continues to work, the probation is deemed to have been passed and the employer may terminate the employment contract with him or her only on other bases prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;d, millel on keelatud naiste rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Work for which employment of women is prohibited </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud on t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tta ja rakendada naisi rasketel ja tervistkahjustavatel t&ouml;&ouml;del ning allmaat&ouml;&ouml;del. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited to hire and employ women for heavy work, work which poses a health hazard or underground work. </inglise>
<eesti>Naistele keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;de loetelu m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks vabariigi valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The list of work which is prohibited for women shall be determined by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;d, millel on keelatud alaealiste rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Work for which employment of minors is prohibited </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud on t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tta ja rakendada alaealisi rasketel, tervistkahjustavatel v&otilde;i ohtlike t&ouml;&ouml;tingimustega t&ouml;&ouml;del ja allmaat&ouml;&ouml;del ning t&ouml;&ouml;del, mis ohustavad alaealiste k&otilde;lblust. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited to hire and employ minors for heavy work, work which poses a health hazard or has dangerous working conditions, underground work, or work which endangers the morality of minors. </inglise>
<eesti>Alaealistele keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;de loetelu m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks vabariigi valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The list of work which is prohibited for minors shall be determined by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohakaaslus (1) </eesti>
<inglise>Second job (3) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohakaasluseks loetakse t&ouml;&ouml;tamist teise t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel v&auml;ljaspool t&ouml;&ouml;aega p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;l sama v&otilde;i teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Work performed on the basis of another employment contract outside of working time in the principal job for the same or another employer is deemed to be a second job. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;leping t&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks kohakaasluses s&otilde;lmitakse samas korras nagu p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employment contract for a second job is entered into in the same manner as for a principal job. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigi- v&otilde;i munitsipaalettev&otilde;tte, -asutuse v&otilde;i muu riigi- v&otilde;i munitsipaalorganisatsiooni juhil, tema aset&auml;itjatel, peaspetsialistidel ning struktuuri&uuml;ksuste juhtidel ja nende aset&auml;itjatel on keelatud kohakaasluse korras t&ouml;&ouml;tamine nii samas ettev&otilde;ttes, asutuses v&otilde;i organisatsioonis kui ka teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures, v&auml;lja arvatud pedagoogiline v&otilde;i teadust&ouml;&ouml;. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) It is prohibited for directors, their deputies, senior experts or heads of structural units of state or municipal enterprises, agencies, or other state or municipal organisations to work in a second job whether in the same enterprise, agency or organisation, or with another employer, with the exception of teaching or research. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja vastutus t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le mittelubamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Employer's liability for not allowing employee to work </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja keeldub t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lminud t&ouml;&ouml;tajat t&ouml;&ouml;le lubamast, v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohtu kaudu n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&auml;itmist ja kokkulepitud palka sunnitud t&ouml;&ouml;lt puudumise aja eest v&otilde;i h&uuml;vitust t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&auml;itmisest keeldumise eest kolme kuu kokkulepitud palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>If an employer prohibits an employee who has entered into an employment contract from working, the employee may demand by a court proceeding performance of the employment contract and for payment of agreed wages for the period of compelled absence from work, or compensation for refusal to perform the employment contract in the amount of three months' agreed wages. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekord, poolte kohustused ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumine </eesti>
<inglise>Internal Procedures, Duties of Parties and Suspension of Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekord </eesti>
<inglise>Internal Procedures </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldeeskiri </eesti>
<inglise>General rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;sisekord m&auml;&auml;rab poolte k&auml;itumisreeglid t&ouml;&ouml;suhetes. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Internal procedures determine the rules of conduct of the parties in employment relationships. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;sisekord v&otilde;ib olla &uuml;hine ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i organisatsiooni k&otilde;igi t&ouml;&ouml;tajate jaoks v&otilde;i erinev struktuuri&uuml;ksuste v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kategooriate l&otilde;ikes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Internal procedures may be the same for all employees of an enterprise, agency or organisation, or may vary for structural units or employees by category. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjad </eesti>
<inglise>Internal work procedure rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;sisekord m&auml;&auml;ratakse t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjadega t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures, kellel on v&auml;hemalt viis t&ouml;&ouml;tajat. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For employers with at least five employees, internal procedures are regulated by internal work procedure rules. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja, v&auml;lja arvatud riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutus, kinnitab t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjad koosk&otilde;lastatult oma asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektoriga. </eesti>
<inglise>Employers, except state and local government administrative agencies, shall approve internal work procedure rules in agreement with the labour inspector of their location (residence). </inglise>
<eesti>(25.01.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 16, 228) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.01.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 16, 228) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirju ei n&otilde;uta t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt, kellel on alla viie t&ouml;&ouml;taja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For employers with less than five employees, internal work procedure rules are not required. </inglise>
<eesti>Niisugune t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorra m&auml;&auml;rata iseseisvalt, arvestades t&ouml;&ouml; ise&auml;rasusi ja t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorrale harilikult esitatavaid n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>Such employers may regulate internal procedure independently, taking into account the particulars of the work and the requirements which are usually applicable to internal procedures. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade sisu </eesti>
<inglise>Content of internal work procedure rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjad peavad kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rama v&auml;hemalt allj&auml;rgneva: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Internal work procedure rules shall, at a minimum, determine the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;aja alguse ja l&otilde;pu eraldi t&auml;isealistele ja alaealistele, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;aja l&otilde;pu puhkep&auml;evade ja riiklike p&uuml;hade eelsetel p&auml;evadel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the beginning and end of working time separately for adults and minors, and the end of working time on days prior to days off and state holidays; </inglise>
<eesti>2) puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks antavad ajad; </eesti>
<inglise>2) time provided for rest and meals; </inglise>
<eesti>3) palga maksmise aja ja koha; </eesti>
<inglise>3) time and place of payment of wages; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;alaste korralduste andmise korra; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the procedure for giving orders pertaining to work; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;kaitse ja tuleohutuse &uuml;ldjuhised. </eesti>
<inglise>5) general instructions on occupational health and safety and on fire hazards. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml; korral v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;aja alguse ja l&otilde;pu, puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks antavad ajad ning &uuml;hest vahetusest teise &uuml;lemineku aja ja korra m&auml;&auml;rata vahetusgraafikutega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of shift work, the beginning and end of working time, time provided for rest and meals, and the time and procedure for alternating shifts may be regulated by shift schedules. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahetusgraafikud kinnitab t&ouml;&ouml;andja. </eesti>
<inglise>Shift schedules shall be approved by employers. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade projekti tutvustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Introduction of draft internal work procedure rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja annab t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade projekti tutvustamiseks ning ettepanekute ja m&auml;rkuste tegemiseks t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele ja neid esindavale organisatsioonile v&auml;hemalt n&auml;dal enne projekti t&ouml;&ouml;inspektorile esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers shall provide draft internal work procedure rules to employees and organisations representing employees for examination, proposals and comments at least one week prior to submission of the draft to a labour inspector. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade projekti kohta tehtud ettepanekud ja m&auml;rkused ei ole t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kohustuslikud, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui need l&auml;htuvad seadusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Proposals and comments made regarding draft internal work procedure rules are not mandatory for employers, unless they arise from law. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.01.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 16, 228) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.01.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 16, 228) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade koosk&otilde;lastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Approval of internal work procedure rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rast paragrahvi 42 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist esitab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade projekti kahes eksemplaris koosk&otilde;lastamiseks oma asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektorile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) After the expiry of the period prescribed in subsection 42 (1), an employer shall submit two original copies of the draft internal work procedure rules to the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer for approval. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektor vaatab esitatud projekti l&auml;bi kahe n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates selle laekumise p&auml;evast, ja teeb sama t&auml;htaja jooksul oma otsuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The labour inspector shall review the submitted draft within two weeks after the date of receipt, and shall render his or her decision within that period. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade koosk&otilde;lastamisel saadab t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor neist &uuml;he koosk&otilde;lastusm&auml;rkusega eksemplari viivitamatult t&ouml;&ouml;andjale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon approval of the internal work procedure rules, the labour inspector shall promptly send one original copy with a notation of approval to the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektor j&auml;tab koosk&otilde;lastamata t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade projekti, mis on vastuolus seaduse v&otilde;i haldusaktiga ja teatab sellest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale viivitamatult kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The labour inspector shall not approve draft internal work procedure rules which are contrary to law or administrative legislation and shall promptly notify the employer thereof in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Entry into force of internal work procedure rules </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjad j&otilde;ustuvad n&auml;dala m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel, arvates eeskirjade t&ouml;&ouml;inspektoriga koosk&otilde;lastamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast kalendrip&auml;evast, kui t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjades ei ole ette n&auml;htud hilisemat j&otilde;ustumisaega. </eesti>
<inglise>Internal work procedure rules enter into force after one week from the calendar day after approval of the internal work procedure rules by a labour inspector unless the internal work procedure rules prescribe a later date of entry into force. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjadega tutvumise tagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Ensuring access to internal work procedure rules </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja peab tagama t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;imaluse igal ajal tutvuda t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjadega. </eesti>
<inglise>Employers shall ensure that employees have access to internal work procedure rules at all times. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade muutmine ja t&auml;iendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Amendment of internal work procedure rules </inglise>
<eesti>Paragrahve 39-45 kohaldatakse ka t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade muutmisel ja t&auml;iendamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>Sections 39-45 also apply upon the amendment of internal work procedure rules. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade vastuolu seaduse, haldusakti v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga </eesti>
<inglise>Internal work procedure rules contrary to law, administrative legislation or collective agreement </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade s&auml;tted, mis on vastuolus seaduse, haldusakti v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga, on kehtetud. </eesti>
<inglise>Provisions of internal work procedure rules which are contrary to law, administrative legislation or a collective agreement are invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of Parties </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte vastastikused kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Reciprocal duties of parties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja on vastastikku kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers and employees have reciprocal duties to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;- ja kollektiivlepingu tingimusi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) comply with the terms of employment contracts and collective agreements; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorra, t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse ning tuleohutuse n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) comply with internal procedures, occupational health, work safety and fire safety requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>(16.06.99 j&otilde;ust.26.07.99 - RT I 1999, 60, 616) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.06.99 entered into force 26.07.99 - RT I 1999, 60, 616) </inglise>
<eesti>3) hoiduma tegudest, mis kahjustavad teise poole vara, ning tegema endast s&otilde;ltuva, et t&ouml;&ouml;s ei kahjustataks kolmandate isikute vara; </eesti>
<inglise>3) refrain from activities which endanger the property of the other party and ensure that the property of third parties is not endangered by the work; </inglise>
<eesti>4) olema teineteise suhtes viisakad; </eesti>
<inglise>4) be respectful towards one another; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&auml;itma seaduses ja haldusaktis ette n&auml;htud muid vastastikuseid t&ouml;&ouml;alaseid kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>5) perform other reciprocal duties pertaining to work which are prescribed by law and administrative legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of employers </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>An employer is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kindlustama t&ouml;&ouml;taja kokkulepitud t&ouml;&ouml;ga ning andma selgelt ja &otilde;igeaegselt vajalikke korraldusi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) provide employees with the work agreed on, and give necessary orders clearly and in a timely manner; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maksma t&ouml;&ouml; eest tasu etten&auml;htud ajal ja suuruses; </eesti>
<inglise>2) pay remuneration for work at the time and in the amount prescribed; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andma etten&auml;htud puhkust ja maksma puhkusetasu; </eesti>
<inglise>3) grant holidays as prescribed and pay holiday pay; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kindlustama ohutud t&ouml;&ouml;tingimused; </eesti>
<inglise>4) ensure safe working conditions; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tutvustama t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmisel, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajal t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorra, t&ouml;&ouml;kaitse ja tuleohutuse n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) acquaint employees with the internal procedures and with occupational health and safety and fire safety requirements upon hiring and during employment; </inglise>
<eesti>5 (1)) korraldama oma kulul t&ouml;&ouml;alast koolitust, kui ta ise muudab t&ouml;&ouml;ks vajalike kutseoskuste (sealhulgas riigikeele ja v&otilde;&otilde;rkeelte oskuse) n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>5 (1)) organise, at the expense of the employer, vocational training if the employer changes the requirements for professional skills (including proficiency in the official language and foreign languages) necessary for performance of the work; </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </inglise>
<eesti>6) kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rama tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; vastuv&otilde;tmise ja praagiks tunnistamise korra; </eesti>
<inglise>6) determine procedures for acceptance of work performed or declaration that it is defective; </inglise>
<eesti>7) t&auml;itma seaduses, haldusaktis ning kollektiiv- ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud muid kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>7) perform other duties which are prescribed by law, administrative legislation, collective agreements and the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of employees </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>A worker is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tegema kokkulepitud t&ouml;&ouml;d ning t&auml;itma ilma erikorralduseta &uuml;lesandeid, mis tulenevad t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomust v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; &uuml;ldisest k&auml;igust; </eesti>
<inglise>1) perform the work agreed on and fulfil, without special orders, tasks which arise from the character of the work or during the general course of the work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;norme ja kinni pidama etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;ajast; </eesti>
<inglise>2) comply with work standards and adhere to the prescribed working time; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &otilde;igeaegselt ja t&auml;pselt t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;andja seaduslikke korraldusi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) comply with legal orders of the employer in a timely manner and precisely; </inglise>
<eesti>4) hoiduma t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures tegudest, mis takistavad teistel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel kohustuste t&auml;itmist v&otilde;i kahjustavad teiste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;i kolmandate isikute vara; </eesti>
<inglise>4) refrain from actions at the workplace of the employer which hinder other employees from performing their duties or endanger the property of other employees or third parties; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teatama t&ouml;&ouml;andjale viivitamatult t&ouml;&ouml;takistustest v&otilde;i nende ohust ning v&otilde;imaluse korral erikorralduseta k&otilde;rvaldama niisugused takistused v&otilde;i nende ohu; </eesti>
<inglise>5) promptly notify the employer of impediments to work or of the threat thereof and, if possible, eliminate such impediments or threat without special orders; </inglise>
<eesti>6) hoidma t&ouml;&ouml;andja &auml;ri- ja tootmissaladust ning mitte osutama t&ouml;&ouml;andjale konkurentsi, sealhulgas mitte t&ouml;&ouml;tama t&ouml;&ouml;andja loata viimase konkurendi juures, kui need kohustused on ette n&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>6) maintain the business and production secrets of the employer and not compete with the employer, including not working for a competitor of the latter without the permission of the employer, if such duties are prescribed by the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Need kohustused lasuvad t&ouml;&ouml;tajal ka p&auml;rast t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamist, kui pooled s&otilde;lmisid niisuguse kokkuleppe ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja maksis t&ouml;&ouml;tajale mainitud kohustuste t&auml;itmise eest eritasu v&otilde;i andis muud h&uuml;vitust; </eesti>
<inglise>The employee has such duties also after termination of the employment contract if the parties entered into such an agreement and the employer paid special remuneration or provided other compensation to the employee for performance of such duties; </inglise>
<eesti>7) t&auml;itma seaduses, haldusaktis ning kollektiiv- ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud muid kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>7) perform other duties which are prescribed by law, administrative legislation, collective agreements and the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(05.05.93 j&otilde;ust.01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441) </eesti>
<inglise>(05.05.93 entered into force 01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetus </eesti>
<inglise>Business trips </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&auml;hetada t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks v&auml;ljapoole t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml; tegemise asukohta mitte kauemaks kui 30 j&auml;rjestikuseks kalendrip&auml;evaks ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud minema niisugusesse t&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers have the right to send employees outside of the location prescribed by the employment contract, in order to perform their duties, for not longer than thirty consecutive calendar days, and employees are required to go on such business trips. </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetus kesta ka kauem. </eesti>
<inglise>By agreement of the parties, business trips may be of longer duration. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetusse ei ole lubatud saata rasedat ja alaealist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is prohibited to send pregnant women and minors on business trips. </inglise>
<eesti>Naist, kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla kolme aastast last, v&otilde;ib saata t&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetusse tema n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>A woman raising a disabled child or child under three years of age may be sent on a business trip with her consent. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetuse aja eest p&auml;evaraha, korteriraha ja s&otilde;iduraha. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Employers are required to pay a daily allowance, accommodation expenses and travel expenses to employees for the duration of business trips. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes mainitud kompensatsioonide suuruse, maksmise tingimused ja korra kehtestab vabariigi valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The amount, conditions of and procedure for payment of the compensation referred to in subsection (3) of this section shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohustuste t&auml;itmine ja &otilde;iguste teostamine </eesti>
<inglise>Performance of duties and exercise of rights </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja t&auml;idab oma kohustusi isiklikult v&otilde;i selleks volitatud isikute kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers perform their duties personally or through persons who have been authorised for this purpose. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&auml;idab oma kohustusi isiklikult. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees perform their duties personally. </inglise>
<eesti>Kodut&ouml;&ouml; tegemisel v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;andja loal kasutada kolmandate isikute abi. </eesti>
<inglise>Employees performing home work may use the assistance of third parties with the permission of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>Riisiko niisuguste kolmandate isikute poolt t&ouml;&ouml;andjale tekitatud kahju eest lasub t&ouml;&ouml;tajal. </eesti>
<inglise>Employees bear the risk for damage caused to the employer by such third parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Oma &otilde;igusi teostavad pooled isiklikult v&otilde;i selleks volitatud esindajate kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The parties exercise their rights personally or through authorised representatives. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohustuste kestus </eesti>
<inglise>Duration of duties </inglise>
<eesti>Paragrahvides 48-50 etten&auml;htud kohustused lasuvad pooltel ka p&auml;rast t&ouml;&ouml;aja l&otilde;ppu ja t&ouml;&ouml;s etten&auml;htud vaheaegadel, v&auml;lja arvatud, kui kohustuse niisugusel ajal t&auml;itmine on vastuolus kohustuse olemusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The parties have the duties prescribed in &sect;&sect; 48-50 after the end of working time and during prescribed work breaks, unless performance of a duty at such time is contrary to the nature of the duty. </inglise>
<eesti>(05.05.93 j&otilde;ust.01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441) </eesti>
<inglise>(05.05.93 entered into force 01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441) </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of suspension of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumine t&auml;hendab t&ouml;&ouml;taja ajutist vabanemist kohustusest teha t&ouml;&ouml;d ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja ajutist vabanemist kohustusest kindlustada t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;ga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Suspension of an employment contract means a temporary relief of an employee from the duty to perform work and a temporary relief of an employer from the duty to provide an employee with work. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumine ei too kaasa t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of an employment contract does not result in termination of the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Seaduses, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud juhtudel ja korras s&auml;ilitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise ajaks palk v&otilde;i makstakse muud h&uuml;vitust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During the suspension of an employment contract, the wages of the employee continue to be paid or other compensation is paid in the cases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law, a collective agreement or the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for suspension of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;leping peatub: </eesti>
<inglise>An employment contract is suspended: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga etten&auml;htud juhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in the cases prescribed by a collective agreement or the employment contract; </inglise>
<eesti>2) poolte kokkuleppel, sealhulgas poolte kokkuleppel antava palgata puhkuse ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) by agreement of the parties, including during the time of holidays without pay granted by agreement of the parties; </inglise>
<eesti>3) puhkuse ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) during holidays; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ajaks, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu; </eesti>
<inglise>4) during the time that the employee is temporarily incapacitated for work; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ajaks, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&auml;itis talle riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsusorgani poolt pandud &uuml;lesandeid v&otilde;i esindas seaduse v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga etten&auml;htud korras t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) during the time that the employee performs duties imposed upon him or her by a state or local government authority, or represents employees pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law or a collective agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>6) seadusliku streigi ajaks, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja osaleb niisuguses streigis seadusega etten&auml;htud korras; </eesti>
<inglise>6) during the time of a legal strike if the employee participates in such strike pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kaitsej&otilde;udude tegevteenistuse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;teenistuse ajaks, kui t&ouml;&ouml;lepingut ei l&otilde;petatud niisugusesse teenistusse kutsumise v&otilde;i astumise t&otilde;ttu ja pooled leppisid kokku peatada t&ouml;&ouml;leping; </eesti>
<inglise>7) during the time of active service in the armed forces or alternative service if the employment contract is not terminated due to conscription or entry into such service and the parties have agreed to suspend the employment contract; </inglise>
<eesti>8) ajaks, mil t&ouml;&ouml;andja n&otilde;uab t&ouml;&ouml;tajalt ebaseaduslikult teist t&ouml;&ouml;d ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja keeldub niisugust t&ouml;&ouml;d tegemast; </eesti>
<inglise>8) during the time that the employer illegally requires the employee to perform other work and the employee refuses to perform such work; </inglise>
<eesti>9) ajaks, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli arestis v&otilde;i vahi all; </eesti>
<inglise>9) during the time that the employee is under arrest or in custody; </inglise>
<eesti>10) ajaks, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli t&ouml;&ouml;lt k&otilde;rvaldatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 56 v&otilde;i 57 alusel v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate distsiplinaarvastutuse seaduse paragrahv 3 punkti 3 alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>10) during the time that the employee is suspended from work pursuant to &sect; 56 or &sect; 57 of this Act or clause 3 3) of the Employees Disciplinary Punishments Act; </inglise>
<eesti>11) ajaks, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli seadusega selleks volitatud riigiorgani v&otilde;i ametiisiku poolt t&ouml;&ouml;lt k&otilde;rvaldatud; </eesti>
<inglise>11) during the time that the employee is suspended from work by a state body or official authorised to do so by law; </inglise>
<eesti>12) muudel juhtudel, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on seadusega etten&auml;htud alustel ajutiselt vabastatud t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>12) in other cases when the employee is temporarily released from performance of his or her duties on the bases prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(05.05.93 j&otilde;ust.01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441) </eesti>
<inglise>(05.05.93 entered into force 01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Joobes t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lt k&otilde;rvaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of intoxicated employee from work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja k&otilde;rvaldab alkoholi-, narkootilises v&otilde;i toksilises joobes t&ouml;&ouml;taja selleks p&auml;evaks (vahetuseks) t&ouml;&ouml;lt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer suspends an employee who is intoxicated by alcohol, narcotics or toxic substances from work for that day (shift). </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;lt k&otilde;rvaldama ka alkoholi, narkootiliste v&otilde;i toksiliste ainete v&otilde;i arstimite j&auml;&auml;kn&auml;htudega, samuti arstimite m&otilde;ju all oleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kui t&ouml;&ouml; n&otilde;uab erilist t&auml;psust, on seotud suurema ohu allika valdamisega v&otilde;i selle vahetus l&auml;heduses t&ouml;&ouml;tamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>The employer is also required to suspend employees with signs of the residual effects of alcohol, narcotic or toxic substances or medicines, and employees who are under the influence of medicines if the job demands particular accuracy, involves control over a major source of danger or working in its immediate vicinity. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud k&auml;esolevas l&otilde;ikes mainitud juhtudel t&ouml;&ouml;tajat t&ouml;&ouml;le mitte lubama. </eesti>
<inglise>In the cases specified in this subsection, the employer is also required to prohibit the employee from coming to work. </inglise>
<eesti>Niisugune t&ouml;&ouml;le mittelubamine on v&otilde;rdsustatud t&ouml;&ouml;lt k&otilde;rvaldamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>Such prohibition is equal to suspension from work. </inglise>
<eesti>(05.05.93 j&otilde;ust.01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441) </eesti>
<inglise>(05.05.93 entered into force 01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale ei maksta tasu aja eest, mil ta oli t&ouml;&ouml;lt k&otilde;rvaldatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employee is not paid remuneration for the time that he or she is suspended from work on the bases prescribed in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lt k&otilde;rvaldamine distsiplinaarasja menetluse ajaks </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension from work for period of disciplinary procedure </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus k&otilde;rvaldada t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lt distsiplinaarasja menetluse ajaks, s&auml;ilitades selle aja eest t&ouml;&ouml;tajale keskmise palga. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer has the right to suspend an employee from work for the period of a disciplinary procedure, and the employee shall continue to receive his or her average wages for that time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Documentation of suspension of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise vormistab t&ouml;&ouml;andja paragrahvi 20 3. l&otilde;ike punktis 4 etten&auml;htud juhtudel t&ouml;&ouml;raamatus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer documents suspension of an employment contract in the employment record book in the cases prescribed in clause 20 (3) 4. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;udel tehakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise kohta lepingus kanne, milles n&auml;idatakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise aluse formuleering viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile ning aeg, milleks leping on peatunud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At the request of the employee, an entry is made in the employment contract concerning suspension of the contract, with a statement of the basis for suspension of the employment contract and reference to the section, subsection and clause of this Act, and the time during which the contract is suspended. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu muutmine </eesti>
<inglise>Amendment of Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu muutmise m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of amendment of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu muutmine on t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud tingimustes muudatuste tegemine, sealhulgas m&otilde;nede tingimuste lepingust v&auml;ljaj&auml;tmine v&otilde;i t&auml;iendavate tingimuste lepingusse v&otilde;tmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Amendment of an employment contract is the making of amendments to the terms determined in the employment contract, including the exclusion of certain terms from the contract or the addition of supplementary terms into the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Muudatuste tegemine t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml; laadis v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; keerukusastmes on t&ouml;&ouml;taja &uuml;leviimine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Transfer of an employee to another position means changes in the nature or level of complexity of work determined in the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja paigutamine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohale samas asulas ei ole teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimine, kui t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus ei ole kokku lepitud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Transfer of an employee to another workplace in the same district is not transfer to another position unless otherwise agreed in the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;taja paigutamine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le v&auml;ljaspool t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud asulat on t&ouml;&ouml;taja &uuml;leviimine teise paikkonda. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Transfer of an employee to another position outside of the locality determined in the employment contract is transfer of the employee to another locality. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu muutmine on lubatud vaid poolte kokkuleppel, v&auml;lja arvatud paragrahvides 61-66 ette n&auml;htud juhtudel, mil t&ouml;&ouml;tajal v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu &uuml;hepoolset muutmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Amendment of an employment contract is only permitted by agreement of the parties, except in the cases prescribed in &sect;&sect; 61-66, where the employee or the employer has the right to claim unilateral amendment of the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 60. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 60. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;leviimine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le poolte kokkuleppel </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer to other position by agreement of parties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja taotlusel teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimisel otsustatakse h&uuml;vituse maksmine ja selle suurus poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon transfer to another position at the request of an employee, the payment and amount of compensation is decided by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja taotlusel t&ouml;&ouml;taja alatiseks teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud tagama t&ouml;&ouml;tajale uuel t&ouml;&ouml;l esimese kuu jooksul v&auml;hemalt endise t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgse keskmise palga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon permanent transfer of an employee to another position at the request of an employer, the employer is required to continue to pay the employee at least his or her average wages in the former position, during the first month of work in the new position. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 61. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 61. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;udmisel teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le alatiseks &uuml;leviimine </eesti>
<inglise>Permanent transfer to other position at request of employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui arsti otsusega on t&ouml;&ouml;tajale senise t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamine tervise t&otilde;ttu vastun&auml;idustatud ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjal on teist t&ouml;&ouml;d, mida t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervis v&otilde;imaldab teha, on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda enda &uuml;leviimist sellisele t&ouml;&ouml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If, by decision of a doctor, continuation in former position by an employee is not advisable for reasons of health and the employer has other work which the health of the employee allows him or her to perform, the employee has the right to claim transfer to such position. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja on s&uuml;&uuml;di t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervise muutumisel selliseks, mis ei luba tal senise t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamist, on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda enda &uuml;leviimist teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le ja selleks vajalikku v&auml;lja&otilde;pet t&ouml;&ouml;andja kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employer is at fault for a change in the health of an employee which prohibits continuation in his or her former position, the employee has the right to claim transfer to another position and vocational training necessary at the expense of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja teise t&ouml;&ouml; tegemise ajal tagab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale endise t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgse keskmise palga. </eesti>
<inglise>The employer shall continue to pay the employee his or her average wages in the former position during the vocational training and employment in the other position. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andjal ei ole v&otilde;imalik t&ouml;&ouml;tajat &uuml;le viia tema tervisele vastavale t&ouml;&ouml;le, l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvi 86 punkt 4 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If it is not possible for an employer to transfer an employee to a position which is suitable to his or her state of health, the employment contract is terminated pursuant to clause 86 4). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;udmisel tema t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutine kergendamine v&otilde;i ajutine &uuml;leviimine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to other position at request of employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on arsti vormistatud haiguslehe alusel &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutist kergendamist v&otilde;i ajutist &uuml;leviimist terviseseisundile vastavale t&ouml;&ouml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee has the right to request from the employer temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to a position suitable to the employee's state of health based on a certificate for sick leave prepared by a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutise kergendamise v&otilde;i terviseseisundile vastavale t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise tagaj&auml;rjel tekkinud palgavahe h&uuml;vitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses (RT 1991, 23, 272; 1999, 7, 113) s&auml;testatud korras, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The difference in wages resulting from temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to a position suitable to the state of health shall be compensated to the employee pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act (RT 1991, 23, 272; 1999, 7, 113), except in the cases prescribed in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja vabastatakse haiguslehel etten&auml;htud ajaks t&ouml;&ouml;st, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) j&auml;rgne t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor on tuvastanud, et t&ouml;&ouml;andjal ei ole v&otilde;imalik t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi ajutiselt kergendada v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajat terviseseisundile vastavale t&ouml;&ouml;le ajutiselt &uuml;le viia. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The employee shall be released from work for the period prescribed in the certificate for sick leave if the labour inspector of the seat (residence) of the employer establishes that it is not possible for the employer to ease the working conditions temporarily or transfer the employee temporarily to a position suitable to his or her state of health. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;st vabastamise aja eest makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kohustusliku ravikindlustuse h&uuml;vitist Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A compulsory medical insurance benefit shall be paid to the employee for the period of release from work pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 63. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 63. </inglise>
<eesti>Raseda t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutine kergendamine v&otilde;i ajutine &uuml;leviimine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to another position of pregnant women </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rasedal on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda arsti vormistatud haiguslehe alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutist kergendamist v&otilde;i ajutist &uuml;leviimist teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Pregnant women have the right to request temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to another position based on a certificate for sick leave prepared by a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitatakse palgavahe Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The difference in wages shall be compensated to the employee pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) j&auml;rgne t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor on tuvastanud, et t&ouml;&ouml;andjal ei ole v&otilde;imalik raseda t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi kergendada v&otilde;i teda kergemale t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;le viia, vabastatakse ta haiguslehel n&auml;idatud ajaks t&ouml;&ouml;st ja makstakse kohustusliku ravikindlustuse h&uuml;vitist Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the labour inspector of the seat (residence) of the employer establishes that it is not possible for the employer to ease the working conditions of the pregnant woman or transfer her to an easier job, she shall be released from work for the period prescribed in the certificate for sick leave and paid a compulsory medical insurance benefit pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 64. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 64. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu tingimuste muutmine seoses tootmise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; &uuml;mberkorraldamisega </eesti>
<inglise>Amendment of terms of employment contract due to reorganisation of production or work </inglise>
<eesti>(09.02.93 j&otilde;ust.12.03.93 - RT 1993, 10, 150) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.02.93 entered into force 12.03.93 - RT I 1993, 10, 150) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus tootmise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; &uuml;mberkorraldamisel muuta t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;tasustamise aluseid ja t&ouml;&ouml;re&zcaron;iimi, teatades sellest t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kirjalikult ette v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers have the right to amend the bases for remuneration of employees and work regimes upon reorganisation of production or work if they notify the employees thereof in writing at least one month in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.02.93 j&otilde;ust.12.03.93 - RT 1993, 10, 150) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.02.93 entered into force 12.03.93 - RT I 1993, 10, 150) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Muudatustega mitten&otilde;ustumisel on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamist (paragrahv 82). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees have the right to demand termination of their employment contracts if they do not consent to amendment thereof (&sect; 82). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 65. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 65. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajutine &uuml;leviimine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le tootmish&auml;davajaduse korral </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary transfer to other position in event of production emergency </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tootmish&auml;davajadus on erakorralistest asjaoludest tingitud vajadus t&ouml;&ouml;taja ajutiseks &uuml;leviimiseks teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A production emergency is the need, arising from extraordinary circumstances, to temporarily transfer an employee to another position. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;taja ajutiselt &uuml;le viia teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employers have the right to temporarily transfer employees to other positions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loodus&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i tootmisavarii &auml;rahoidmiseks v&otilde;i nende tagaj&auml;rgede kiireks k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for the prevention of a natural disaster or industrial accident or the expeditious elimination of the consequences thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;nnetusjuhtumi, t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku, t&ouml;&ouml;andja vara h&auml;vimise v&otilde;i riknemise &auml;rahoidmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for the prevention of an accident, work stoppage, or destruction of or damage to the property of the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ajutiselt &auml;raoleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja asendamiseks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi punktides 1 ja 2 etten&auml;htud juhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) for the replacement of an employee who is temporarily absent in the cases prescribed in clauses 1) and 2) of this section; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muudel erakorralistel juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in other extraordinary cases. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;leviimine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhtudel on lubatud &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik millisele t&ouml;&ouml;le samas asulas mitte kauemaks kui &uuml;heks kuuks, kui see t&ouml;&ouml; ei ole vastun&auml;idustatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervisele ja ei too kaasa t&ouml;&ouml;taja suuremat materiaalset vastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Transfer to another position in the cases specified in subsection (2) of this section is permitted to any position in the same locality for not longer than one month unless the employee is advised not to accept such position for reasons of health and unless such position results in greater proprietary liability for the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teisel t&ouml;&ouml;l makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale tasu tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgi, kuid mitte v&auml;hem keskmisest palgast endisel t&ouml;&ouml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the other position, the employee is paid remuneration according to the position, but not less than his or her average wages in the former position. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 66. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 66. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajutine &uuml;leviimine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku korral </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary transfer to other position in case of work stoppage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;seisak on t&ouml;&ouml; seiskumine t&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks vajalike organisatsiooniliste v&otilde;i tehniliste tingimuste puudumise, v&auml;&auml;ramatu j&otilde;u v&otilde;i muude asjaolude t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Work stoppage is the stopping of work due to a lack of necessary organisational or technical conditions, force majeure or other circumstances. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;seisaku ajaks on t&ouml;&ouml;andjal &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;taja &uuml;le viia &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik millisele t&ouml;&ouml;le samas asulas, kui see t&ouml;&ouml; ei ole vastun&auml;idustatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervisele ja ei too kaasa t&ouml;&ouml;taja suuremat materiaalset vastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During a work stoppage an employer has the right to transfer an employee to any position in the same locality unless the employee is advised not to accept such position for reasons of health and unless such position results in greater proprietary liability for the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes ei ole s&uuml;&uuml;di t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku tekkimises, makstakse teisel t&ouml;&ouml;l tasu t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgi, kuid mitte v&auml;hem keskmisest palgast endisel t&ouml;&ouml;l, tingimusel, et ta t&auml;idab t&ouml;&ouml;norme. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employee who is not at fault for a work stoppage is paid remuneration according to the other position but not less than his or her average wages in the former position, provided that he or she fulfils the production quota. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;normide mittet&auml;itmisel, kui see pole tingitud t&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;st, makstakse talle tasu vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;le, kuid mitte v&auml;hem tunnipalgam&auml;&auml;rast endisel t&ouml;&ouml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>If the production quota is not fulfilled through no fault of the employee, he or she is paid remuneration according to the position, but not less than at the rate of hourly wages in the former position. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes on s&uuml;&uuml;di t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku tekkimises, makstakse tasu t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employee who is at fault for a work stoppage is paid remuneration according to the position. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 67. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 67. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja ajutine &uuml;leviimine teise ettev&otilde;ttesse, asutusse v&otilde;i muusse organisatsiooni riigivalitsemis- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsusorgani otsusel </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary transfer of employee to other enterprise, agency or other organisation by decision of state or local government authority </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus riigivalitsemisorgani otsuse alusel viia t&ouml;&ouml;taja ajutiselt &uuml;le t&ouml;&ouml;le teise ettev&otilde;ttesse, asutusse v&otilde;i muusse organisatsiooni samas asulas v&otilde;i teise paikkonda loodus&otilde;nnetuse ennetamiseks, selle tagaj&auml;rgede kiireks k&otilde;rvaldamiseks v&otilde;i haiguste leviku t&otilde;kestamiseks, kuid mitte kauemaks kui &uuml;heks kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On the basis of a decision of a state authority, an employer has the right to temporarily transfer an employee to a position at another enterprise, agency or other organisation in the same or another locality for the prevention of a natural disaster, expeditious elimination of the consequences thereof or prevention of the spread of disease, but for not more than one month. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhtudel kohaliku omavalitsusorgani otsuse alusel &otilde;igus samaks t&auml;htajaks t&ouml;&ouml;taja &uuml;le viia t&ouml;&ouml;le teise ettev&otilde;ttesse, asutusse v&otilde;i muusse organisatsiooni otsuse teinud omavalitsusorgani haldamisel oleva territooriumi piires. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the cases specified in subsection (1) of this section, an employer has the right to transfer an employee to another enterprise, agency or other organisation for the same period, on the basis of a decision of a local government authority, within the boundaries of the territory administered by the local government authority which made the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;leviimine k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. ja 2. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhtudel on lubatud &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik millisele t&ouml;&ouml;le, kui see ei ole vastun&auml;idustatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervisele ja ei too kaasa t&ouml;&ouml;taja suuremat materiaalset vastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the cases specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section, transfer is permitted to any position unless an employee is advised not to accept such position for reasons of health and unless such position results in greater proprietary liability for the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. ja 2. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhtudel ei ole lubatud teise paikkonda &uuml;le viia rasedat, naist, kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla 16-aastast last, samuti alaealist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the cases specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section, it is not permitted to transfer a pregnant woman, a woman who is raising a disabled child or a child under sixteen years of age, or a minor to another locality. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. ja 2. l&otilde;ike alusel &uuml;le viidud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale makstakse tasu t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgi, kuid mitte v&auml;hem keskmisest palgast endisel t&ouml;&ouml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An employee transferred pursuant to subsections (1) and (2) of this section is paid remuneration according to the position, but not less than his or her average wages in the former position. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 68. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 68. </inglise>
<eesti>Osalise t&ouml;&ouml;aja rakendamine v&otilde;i osaliselt tasustatava puhkuse andmine t&ouml;&ouml;mahu v&otilde;i tellimuste ajutisel v&auml;henemisel </eesti>
<inglise>Application of part-time working time or grant of holidays with partial pay upon temporary decrease in work volume or orders </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;mahu v&otilde;i tellimuste ajutisel v&auml;henemisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andjal oma asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul &otilde;igus kokkuleppel t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga kehtestada t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kuni kolmeks kuuks aastas osaline t&ouml;&ouml;aeg v&otilde;i saata t&ouml;&ouml;taja osaliselt tasustatavale puhkusele samaks t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon a temporary decrease in work volume or orders, an employer has the right, with the consent of the labour inspector of his or her location (residence), to establish part-time working time for an employee for up to three months per year or to send the employee on a holiday with partial pay for the same period with the agreement of the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektorilt n&otilde;usoleku taotlemisel esitab t&ouml;&ouml;andja p&otilde;hjenduse t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamise v&otilde;imaluste kohta ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindava organisatsiooni v&otilde;i isiku arvamuse. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon applying for the consent of the labour inspector, the employer shall present a justification regarding the possibilities for continuation of work and the opinion of the organisation or person representing the employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Osalise t&ouml;&ouml;aja kehtestamisest v&otilde;i osaliselt tasustatavale puhkusele saatmisest on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud teatama t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer is required to give an employee at least two weeks' advance notice in writing of the application of part-time working time or sending him or her on a holiday with partial pay. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;korralduse nimetatud muudatustega mitten&otilde;ustumisel on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamist paragrahv 82 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>The employee has the right to demand termination of the employment contract pursuant to &sect; 82 if he or she does not consent to such changes in work organisation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi alusel rakendatava osalise t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestus ei v&otilde;i olla alla 60% t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;aja normaalkestusest ja osaliselt tasustatava puhkuse ajal makstav puhkusetasu ei v&otilde;i olla v&auml;iksem kui 60% miinimumpalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The duration of part-time working time applied pursuant to this section shall not be less than 60 per cent of the standard working time prescribed in the employment contract, and the holiday pay payable during holidays with partial pay shall not be less than 60 per cent of the minimum wage. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ette teatada tema koondamisest ajal, mil talle on kehtestatud osaline t&ouml;&ouml;aeg v&otilde;i ta on saadetud osaliselt tasustatavale puhkusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) It is prohibited for an employer to notify an employee in advance of his or her lay-off during the time when part-time working time is applied for him or her, or when he or she has been sent on a holiday with partial pay. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kehtestada osalist t&ouml;&ouml;aega v&otilde;i saata teda osaliselt tasustatavale puhkusele ajal, mil talle on ette teatatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 86 punkti 3 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) It is prohibited for an employer to apply part-time working time for an employee or to send an employee on a holiday with partial pay at a time when he or she has been notified in advance of the termination of the employment contract pursuant to clause 86 3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja rakendab osalist t&ouml;&ouml;aega v&otilde;i saadab t&ouml;&ouml;taja osaliselt tasustatavale puhkusele ilma t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekuta, siis on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale maksma h&uuml;vitust saamata j&auml;&auml;nud palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If an employer applies part-time working time or sends an employee on a holiday with partial pay without the consent of the employee or the labour inspector, the employer is required to pay compensation to the employee in the amount of unpaid wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.02.93 j&otilde;ust.12.03.93 - RT 1993, 10, 150) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.02.93 entered into force 12.03.93 - RT I 1993, 10, 150) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 69. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 69. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste seadusevastase muutmise ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja seadusliku korralduse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability for illegal amendment of working conditions and failure to comply with legal orders of employer </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja seadusevastaselt viib t&ouml;&ouml;taja &uuml;le teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;i muudab muid t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu tingimusi, on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda ennistamist endisele t&ouml;&ouml;le, samuti muude kokkulepitud t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste taastamist ning kuni nende seaduserikkumiste k&otilde;rvaldamiseni saamata j&auml;&auml;nud t&ouml;&ouml;tasu maksmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an employer illegally transfers an employee to another position or amends other terms of the employment contract, the employee has the right to demand reinstatement in his or her former position, restoration of other working conditions agreed on and payment of wages which were not received until the elimination of such violations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja j&auml;tab oma s&uuml;&uuml; t&otilde;ttu t&auml;itmata t&ouml;&ouml;andja seadusliku korralduse teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise kohta, on ta kohustatud h&uuml;vitama t&ouml;&ouml;andjale sellega tekitatud kahju, kuid mitte rohkem kui oma &uuml;he kuu keskmise palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If, due to his or her own fault, an employee fails to comply with legal orders of the employer regarding transfer to another position, he or she is required to compensate the employer for damage caused thereby, but for not more than the amount of his or her one month's average wages. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 70. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 70. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu tingimuste muutmise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalisation of amendments to terms of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu tingimuste muutmine vormistatakse kirjalikult t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>Amendments to terms of an employment contract are formalised in writing in the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudatustele kirjutavad alla t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;i tema esindaja ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja. </eesti>
<inglise>The employer or his or her representative and the employee shall sign the amendments. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 71. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 71. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for termination of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;peb: </eesti>
<inglise>An employment contract terminates: </inglise>
<eesti>1) poolte kokkuleppel (paragrahv 76); </eesti>
<inglise>1) by agreement of the parties (&sect; 76); </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel (paragrahv 77); </eesti>
<inglise>2) upon expiry of the term (&sect; 77); </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;taja algatusel (paragrahvid 79, 80, 82 ja 85); </eesti>
<inglise>3) on the initiative of the employee (&sect;&sect; 79, 80, 82 and 85); </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel (paragrahv 86); </eesti>
<inglise>4) on the initiative of the employer (&sect; 86); </inglise>
<eesti>5) kolmandate isikute n&otilde;udmisel (paragrahv 110); </eesti>
<inglise>5) at the request of third parties (&sect; 110); </inglise>
<eesti>6) pooltest s&otilde;ltumatutel asjaoludel (paragrahvid 111-116). </eesti>
<inglise>6) in circumstances which are independent of the parties (&sect;&sect; 111-116). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 72. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 72. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest etteteatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Advance notice of termination of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest teineteisele ette teatama kirjalikult (paragrahvid 77, 79, 80, 82, 85 ja 87). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers and employees are required to give each other advance notice in writing of the termination of an employment contract (&sect;&sect; 77, 79, 80, 82, 85 and 87). </inglise>
<eesti>Soov l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping peab olema v&auml;ljendatud tingimusteta. </eesti>
<inglise>A request to terminate an employment contract shall be expressed unconditionally. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamiseks esitatud kirjalikust teatisest v&otilde;ib loobuda teise poole n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Written notice of termination of an employment contract may be waived with the consent of the other party. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 73. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 73. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalisation of termination of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja teeb t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise kohta lepingusse kande, milles n&auml;idatakse lepingu l&otilde;petamise aluse formuleering viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&auml;ev, t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjale h&uuml;vituse maksmine ja lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu tagastamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer makes an entry regarding the termination of an employment contract in the employment contract, with a statement of the basis for termination of the contract and reference to the section, subsection and clause of this Act, the date of termination of the employment contract, payment of compensation to the employee or employer and return of that which was acquired under the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&auml;evaks on t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;loleku viimane p&auml;ev, kui k&auml;esolev seadus ei n&auml;e ette teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The date of termination of an employment contract is the last date on which the employee is at work unless this Act prescribes otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on enne t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamist lahkunud t&ouml;&ouml;lt omavoliliselt, siis l&otilde;petab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu p&auml;evast, mis j&auml;rgnes p&auml;evale, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lt omavoliliselt lahkus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an employee has left work prior to the termination of the employment contract without authorisation, the employer terminates the employment contract with the employee as of the date following the date on which the employee left without authorisation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 74. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 74. </inglise>
<eesti>Kande tegemine t&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse ja l&otilde;pparve maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Making entry in employment record book and payment of final settlement </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja teeb t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise kohta t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse kande, milles n&auml;idatakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer makes an entry in the employment record book of an employee regarding the termination of the employment contract, indicating the date of termination of the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise aluse formuleeringu viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile kannab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse t&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;udel. </eesti>
<inglise>At the request of the employee, the employer enters a statement of the basis for termination of the employment contract and reference to the section, subsection and clause of this Act in the employee's employment record book. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud andma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu ja maksma l&otilde;pparve t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer is required to return an employee's employment record book to the employee and to pay the final settlement on the date of termination of the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;raamatut v&otilde;i l&otilde;pparvet vastu ei v&otilde;tnud, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud andma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu n&otilde;ude esitamise p&auml;eval ja maksma l&otilde;pparve viie kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates n&otilde;ude esitamisele j&auml;rgnenud p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>If the employee does not accept the employment record book or final settlement on the date of termination of the employment contract, the employer is required to return the employment record book to the employee on the date the employee makes such request and to pay the final settlement within five calendar days after the date following the making of the request. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 75. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 75. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of termination of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja - f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik - registreerib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise oma elukoha t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori juures &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer who is a natural person shall register termination of an employment contract with the labour inspector of his or her residence within one week after the date following the date of termination of the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine poolte kokkuleppel ja t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of Employment Contract by Agreement of Parties and upon Expiry of Term </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 76. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 76. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine poolte kokkuleppel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract by agreement of parties </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petada igal ajal, kui &uuml;ks pooltest esitab vastavasisulise kirjaliku taotluse ja teine pool annab lepingu l&otilde;petamiseks kirjaliku n&otilde;usoleku. </eesti>
<inglise>By agreement of the parties, an employment contract may be terminated at any time if one party presents a corresponding written request and the other party gives written consent to termination of the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 77. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 77. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon expiry of term </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise t&otilde;ttu, teatades t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest kirjalikult: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer may terminate an employment contract due to expiry of its term if the employer gives notice of termination of the employment contract in writing: </inglise>
<eesti>1) v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat enne t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist, kui lepingut&auml;htaeg &uuml;letab &uuml;hte aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) at least two weeks prior to the expiry of the term, if the term of the contract exceeds one year; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&auml;hemalt viis kalendrip&auml;eva enne t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist, kui lepingut&auml;htaeg ei &uuml;leta &uuml;hte aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>2) at least five calendar days prior to expiry of the term, if the term of the contract does not exceed one year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaegu ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga, kes on t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;etud &auml;raoleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja asendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The periods prescribed in subsection (1) of the section are not applied upon termination of an employment contract with an employee who was hired for replacement of an absent employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja, kes ei j&auml;rginud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud etteteatamist&auml;htaegu, on kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitusena keskmist p&auml;evapalka etteteatamist&auml;htajast puudu j&auml;&auml;va iga t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer who does not comply with the terms for advance notice prescribed in subsection (1) of this section is required to pay compensation in the amount of the average daily wages to the employee for each working day short of the period for advance notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;ib l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise t&otilde;ttu, teatades t&ouml;&ouml;andjale t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest v&auml;hemalt viis kalendrip&auml;eva enne lepingut&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employee may terminate his or her employment contract due to expiry of its term if the employee gives notice of termination of the employment contract at least five calendar days prior to expiry of the term of the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest t&ouml;&ouml;andjat ei hoiatanud ja j&auml;&auml;b lepingut&auml;htaja viimasele p&auml;evale vahetult j&auml;rgneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;lt &auml;ra, peab t&ouml;&ouml;andja andma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu ja maksma l&otilde;pparve hiljemalt viie kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, mis j&auml;rgnes p&auml;evale, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja mainitud n&otilde;ude esitas. </eesti>
<inglise>If the employee does not warn the employer of termination of the employment contract and is absent from work on the next working day following the last date of the term of the contract, the employer shall return the employment record book to the employee and pay the final settlement not later than within five calendar days after the date which followed the date on which the employee presented a request therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 78. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 78. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu muutumine m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguks </eesti>
<inglise>Transformation of employment contract entered into for specified term into employment contract entered into for unspecified term </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kumbki pooltest ei n&otilde;ua m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamist paragrahvis 77 etten&auml;htud korras v&otilde;i ei s&otilde;lmita uut t&ouml;&ouml;lepingut ja t&ouml;&ouml;suhted j&auml;tkuvad ka p&auml;rast lepingut&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist, muutub m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;leping m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguks. </eesti>
<inglise>If neither party demands termination of an employment contract entered into for a specified term pursuant to the procedure prescribed in &sect; 77, or if a new employment contract is not entered into and the employment relationship continues after expiry of the term of the contract, then the employment contract for a specified term becomes an employment contract entered into for an unspecified term. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja algatusel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of Employment Contract on Initiative of Employee </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 79. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 79. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja algatusel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract entered into for unspecified term on initiative of employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) M&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest teatab t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee shall give an employer at least one month's advance notice of termination of his or her employment contract entered into for an unspecified term. </inglise>
<eesti>Katseaja kestel on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petada, teatades sellest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kolm kalendrip&auml;eva ette. </eesti>
<inglise>During a probationary period, an employee has the right to terminate his or her employment contract if the employee gives notice to the employer thereof three calendar days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&otilde;hjuseks on t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamist takistav haigus, invaliidsus, haige v&otilde;i invaliidistunud perekonnaliikme hooldamise vajadus v&otilde;i &otilde;ppima asumine, teatab t&ouml;&ouml;taja lepingu l&otilde;petamisest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&auml;hemalt viis kalendrip&auml;eva ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the reason for termination of an employment contract entered into for an unspecified term is an illness, disability, need to care for a family member who is ill or disabled, or commencement of studies, which hinders continuation of work, the employee shall notify the employer of the termination of the employment contract at least five calendar days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>Samas korras v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petada ka naine, kes kasvatab alla kolmeaastast last. </eesti>
<inglise>A woman raising a child under three years of age may terminate her employment contract by the same procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 80. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 80. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja algatusel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract entered into for specified term on initiative of employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu (paragrahvi 27 2. l&otilde;ige, punktid 1-4 ja 6) ennet&auml;htaegsest l&otilde;petamisest teatab t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale ette v&auml;hemalt: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee shall notify an employer of premature termination of an employment contract entered into for a specified term (clauses 27 (2) 1) -4) and 6)) at least: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kaks n&auml;dalat, kui lepingu t&auml;htaeg &uuml;letab &uuml;hte aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) two weeks in advance if the term of the contract exceeds one year; </inglise>
<eesti>2) viis kalendrip&auml;eva, kui lepingu t&auml;htaeg ei &uuml;leta &uuml;hte aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>2) five calendar days in advance if the term of the contract does not exceed one year; </inglise>
<eesti>3) viis kalendrip&auml;eva, kui lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&otilde;hjuseks on t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamist takistav haigus, invaliidsus, haige v&otilde;i invaliidistunud perekonnaliikme hooldamise vajadus v&otilde;i &otilde;ppima asumine. </eesti>
<inglise>3) five calendar days in advance if the reason for termination of the employment contract is an illness, disability, need to care for a family member who is ill or disabled, or commencement of studies, which hinders continuation of work. </inglise>
<eesti>Samas korras v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petada ka naine, kes kasvatab alla kolmeaastast last. </eesti>
<inglise>A woman raising a child under three years of age may terminate her employment contract by the same procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud erisoodustustega t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu (paragrahvi 27 2. l&otilde;ike punkt 5) ennet&auml;htaegse l&otilde;petamise p&otilde;hjuseks on t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamist takistav haigus, invaliidsus v&otilde;i invaliidistunud perekonnaliikme hooldamise vajadus, teatab t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale lepingu l&otilde;petamisest v&auml;hemalt viis kalendrip&auml;eva ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the reason for premature termination of an employment contract entered into for a specified term with special benefits (clause 27 (2) 5)) is an illness, disability or need to care for a family member who is disabled, which hinders continuation of work, the employee shall notify the employer of the termination of the contract at least five calendar days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudel p&otilde;hjustel niisugust t&ouml;&ouml;lepingut t&ouml;&ouml;taja algatusel ei l&otilde;petata. </eesti>
<inglise>Such employment contract is not terminated on the initiative of an employee for other reasons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 81. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 81. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&otilde;hjuse t&otilde;endamine </eesti>
<inglise>Proof of reason for termination of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamiseks paragrahv 79 2. l&otilde;ikes ning paragrahv 80 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 3 ja 2. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud alustel esitab t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kirjaliku t&otilde;endi lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&otilde;hjuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>For termination of an employment contract on the bases prescribed in subsection 79 (2), clause 80 (1) 3) and subsection 80 (2), an employee shall present written proof of the reason for termination of the contract to the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 82. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 82. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolse lepingutingimuste rikkumise v&otilde;i tootmis- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;korralduses tehtud muudatuste t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract due to violation of contractual terms by employer or changes in production or work organisation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja teatab nii m&auml;&auml;ramata kui m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&auml;hemalt viis kalendrip&auml;eva ette, kui lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&otilde;hjuseks on t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolne lepingu tingimuste t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmine, mitten&otilde;uetekohane t&auml;itmine v&otilde;i muudatused tootmis- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;korralduses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee shall notify the employer of the termination of his or her employment contract entered into for an unspecified or specified term at least five calendar days in advance if the reason for termination of the contract is failure to comply or unsatisfactory compliance with the terms of the contract by the employer, or changes in production or work organisation. </inglise>
<eesti>Nendel juhtudel (paragrahvid 64 ja 68) l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;leping niisuguste muudatuste rakendamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>In such cases (&sect;&sect; 64 and 68) an employment contract is terminated as of the date of the implementation of such changes. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitusena tema kahe kuu keskmise palga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon termination of an employment contract entered into for an unspecified term pursuant to subsection (1) of this section, the employer shall pay to the employee compensation in the amount of his or her two months' average wages. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel samal alusel maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale tema keskmise palga lepingu t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumiseni, kuid mitte &uuml;le kahe kuu. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon termination of an employment contract entered into for a specified term on the same basis, the employer shall pay to the employee compensation in the amount of his or her average wages until expiry of the term of the contract, but for not more than two months. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 83. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 83. </inglise>
<eesti>Etteteatamist&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise tagaj&auml;rjed </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of expiry of term for advance notice </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Etteteatamist&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;taja lahkuda t&ouml;&ouml;lt ning t&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud andma talle t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu ja l&otilde;pparve, v&auml;lja arvatud paragrahvi 80 2. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon expiry of a term for advance notice, an employee may cease employment and the employer is required to return the employment record book and pay the final settlement to him or her, except in the cases prescribed in subsection 80 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Paragrahvi 80 2. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud juhtudel v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lt lahkuda p&auml;rast t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise vormistamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the cases prescribed in subsection 80 (2), an employee may cease employment after formalisation of the termination of the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte vaidluse korral lahkumise p&otilde;hjuse &uuml;le lahendab k&uuml;simuse t&ouml;&ouml;vaidlusorgan. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of a dispute between the parties over the reason for leaving, the issue is resolved by a labour dispute resolution body. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;suhete j&auml;tkumisel p&auml;rast etteteatamist&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist ei v&otilde;i pooled varem esitatud avalduse alusel t&ouml;&ouml;lepingut &uuml;hepoolselt l&otilde;petada. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon continuation of an employment relationship after expiry of the term for advance notice, the parties shall not unilaterally terminate the employment contract on the basis of a previously presented application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 84. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 84. </inglise>
<eesti>Enne etteteatamist&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise tagaj&auml;rjed </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of termination of employment contract prior to expiry of term for advance notice </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja, kes vabastab t&ouml;&ouml;taja tema kirjaliku n&otilde;usolekuta enne etteteatamist&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist, on kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitusena keskmise p&auml;evapalga etteteatamist&auml;htajast puudu j&auml;&auml;va iga t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer who releases an employee without his or her written consent prior to expiry of the term for advance notice is required to pay compensation to the employee in the amount of the employee's average daily wages for each working day short of the term for advance notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda enne etteteatamist&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist omavoliliselt lahkunud t&ouml;&ouml;tajalt h&uuml;vitusena keskmist p&auml;evapalka etteteatamist&auml;htajast puudu j&auml;&auml;va iga t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer has the right to demand compensation from an employee who has left without authorisation prior to the expiry of the term for advance notice in the amount of the employee's average daily wages for each working day short of the term for advance notice. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 85. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 85. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja asumisel valitavale ametikohale </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon employee assuming elected office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja asumisel ametikohale, mis t&auml;idetakse valimise v&otilde;i nimetamise teel, l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;leping t&ouml;&ouml;taja avalduse alusel hiljemalt mainitud ametikohale asumise p&auml;evale vahetult eelnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an employee assumes an office which is filled by election or appointment, the employment contract is terminated at the request of the employee not later than the date directly preceding the date of assumption of such office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja valimisel Eesti k&otilde;rgeima riigiv&otilde;imuorgani liikmeks l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;leping t&ouml;&ouml;taja avalduse alusel tema saadikumandaadi tunnustamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employee is elected as a member of the supreme state authority of Estonia, the employment contract is terminated at the request of the employee as of the date of acknowledgement of his or her mandate. </inglise>
<eesti>4. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 4 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of Employment Contract on Initiative of Employer </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 86. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 86. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for termination of employment contract on initiative of employer </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib l&otilde;petada m&auml;&auml;ramata kui ka m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu enne lepingut&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist: </eesti>
<inglise>An employer may terminate an employment contract entered into for an unspecified or specified term prior to expiry of the term of the contract: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni likvideerimisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) upon liquidation of the enterprise, agency or other organisation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;andja pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) upon the declaration of bankruptcy of the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>(18.12.96 j&otilde;ust.01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.12.96 entered into force 01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajate koondamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) upon lay-off of employees; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;taja mittevastavusel oma ametikohale v&otilde;i tehtavale t&ouml;&ouml;le t&ouml;&ouml;oskuse v&otilde;i tervise t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>4) upon unsuitability of an employee for his or her office or the work to be performed due to professional skills or for reasons of health; </inglise>
<eesti>5) katseaja ebarahuldavate tulemuste t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>5) due to unsatisfactory results of a probationary period; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&ouml;&ouml;tajapoolsel t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste rikkumisel; </eesti>
<inglise>6) upon breach of duties an employee; </inglise>
<eesti>7) t&ouml;&ouml;taja suhtes usalduse kaotamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>7) upon loss of trust in an employee; </inglise>
<eesti>8) t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&auml;&auml;ritu teo t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>8) due to an indecent act by an employee; </inglise>
<eesti>9) t&ouml;&ouml;taja pikaajalise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>9) due to the long-term incapacity for work of an employee; </inglise>
<eesti>10) t&ouml;&ouml;taja vanuse t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>10) due to the age of an employee; </inglise>
<eesti>11) p&otilde;hikohaga t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>11) upon hiring an employee for whom the position is a principal job; </inglise>
<eesti>12) t&ouml;&ouml;taja korruptiivse teo t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>12) due to an act of corruption of an employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 87. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 87. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest etteteatamine ja p&otilde;hjendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Advance notice to employee of termination of employment contract, and justification of termination thereof </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kirjalikult ette teatama: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer is required to notify an employee of termination of the employment contract in writing: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni likvideerimisel - mitte v&auml;hem kui kaks kuud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) not less than two months in advance upon liquidation of the enterprise, agency or other organisation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) (Kehtetu - 18.12.96 j&otilde;ust.01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </eesti>
<inglise>2) (Repealed - 18.12.96 entered into force 01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajate koondamisel: t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kellel on pidevat t&ouml;&ouml;staa&zcaron;i selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures alla viie aasta - mitte v&auml;hem kui kaks kuud; </eesti>
<inglise>3) upon lay-off of employees: not less than two months in advance if the employee has been continuously employed by the employer for less than five years; not less than three months in advance if the employee has been continuously employed by the employer for five to ten years; </inglise>
<eesti>5-10 aastat - mitte v&auml;hem kui kolm kuud; &uuml;le 10 aasta - mitte v&auml;hem kui neli kuud; </eesti>
<inglise>not less than four months in advance if the employee has been continuously employed by the employer for more than ten years; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;taja mittevastavusel oma ametikohale v&otilde;i tehtavale t&ouml;&ouml;le - mitte v&auml;hem kui &uuml;ks kuu; </eesti>
<inglise>4) not less than one month in advance upon unsuitability of the employee for his or her office or the work to be performed; </inglise>
<eesti>5) pikaajalise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse korral - mitte v&auml;hem kui kaks n&auml;dalat; </eesti>
<inglise>5) not less than two weeks in advance in the case of long-term incapacity for work; </inglise>
<eesti>6) vanuse puhul t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kellel on pidevat t&ouml;&ouml;staa&zcaron;i selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures alla 10 aasta - kaks kuud; &uuml;le 10 aasta - kolm kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>6) due to age, two months in advance if the employee has been continuously employed by the employer for less than ten years; three months in advance if the employee has been continuously employed by the employer for more than ten years. </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Kirjalikus teates t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise kohta on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud p&otilde;hjendama t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise vajadust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) In a written notice concerning termination of an employment contract, the employer is required to justify the need to terminate the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. ja 5. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaegade mittej&auml;rgimisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitust keskmise p&auml;evapalga ulatuses iga t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva eest, mille v&otilde;rra t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest v&auml;hem ette teatati. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon failure to adhere to the terms prescribed in subsections (1) and (5) of this section, an employer is required to pay compensation to the employee in the amount of the employee's average daily wages for each working day short of advance notice of termination of the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Mainitud h&uuml;vituse maksmine ei vabasta t&ouml;&ouml;andjat kohustusest maksta t&ouml;&ouml;tajale paragrahvi 90 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud h&uuml;vitust. </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of such compensation does not release the employer of the duty to pay the employee the compensation prescribed in subsection 90 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud alustel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud sellest kirjalikult ette teatama ka t&ouml;&ouml;tajat esindavale organisatsioonile v&otilde;i isikule samas l&otilde;ikes n&auml;idatud t&auml;htajal (v&auml;lja arvatud 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 6) ja esitama lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&otilde;hjuse ning tegema teatavaks abin&otilde;ud, mis ta on tarvitusele v&otilde;tnud t&ouml;&ouml;taja edaspidiseks t&ouml;&ouml;ga kindlustamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon termination of an employment contract on the bases specified in subsection (1) of this section, an employer is required to give advance notice thereof in writing to the organisation or person representing the employee within the term specified in the same subsection (except clause 87 (1) 6)) and to present the reason for termination of the contract and communicate the measures taken to provide work for the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andja pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamisel on lubatud t&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ette teatamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon the declaration of bankruptcy of an employer, it is permitted to terminate employment contracts without advance notice to the employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.12.96 j&otilde;ust.01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.12.96 entered into force 01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajaga on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud talle kirjalikult ette teatama k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1.l&otilde;ike punktides 3 ja 4 etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaegadest &uuml;ks kuu varem. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An employer who terminates an employment contract with a representative of employees is required to give advance notice to the representative in writing one month earlier than the terms prescribed in clauses (1) 3) and 4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 88. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 88. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametile t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notice to employment office of termination of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i organisatsiooni likvideerimise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate koondamise t&otilde;ttu on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud esitama andmed vabanevate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kohta t&ouml;&ouml;taja elukohaj&auml;rgsele t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametile hiljemalt j&auml;rgmisel p&auml;eval, kui ta on teatanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon termination of employment contracts due to the liquidation of an enterprise, agency or organisation, or the lay-off of employees, the employer is required to submit information regarding the released employees to the employment office of the residence of the employees not later than on the day after the employer notifies the employees of the termination of their employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega t&ouml;&ouml;andaja pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamisel, esitab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kohta andmed t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametile t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisele j&auml;rgneval p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>If employment contracts are terminated with employees upon the declaration of bankruptcy of the employer, the employer shall submit information regarding the employees to the employment office on the date following termination of the employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.10.2000 - RT I 2000, 57, 370) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 01.10.2000 - RT I 2000, 57, 370) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise peatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of termination of employment contract on initiative of employer </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja kavatseb l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&ouml;&ouml;tajate koondamise t&otilde;ttu 10-20 t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga kolme kuu jooksul ja vabanevate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;lepaigutamine ei ole tagatud, v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindav organisatsioon v&otilde;i isik lepingu l&otilde;petamise peatada kuni &uuml;heks kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>If an employer intends to terminate employment contracts with ten to twenty employees during a three month period due to a lay-off of employees and job placements for the released employees are not ensured, the organisation or person representing the employees may suspend termination of the contracts for up to one month. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui koondamise t&otilde;ttu vabaneb kolme kuu jooksul &uuml;le 20 t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja vabanevate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;lepaigutamine ei ole tagatud, v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindav organisatsioon v&otilde;i isik t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise peatada kuni kaheks kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>If more than twenty employees are released during a three month period due to a lay-off and job placements are not ensured for the released employees, the organisation or person representing the employees may suspend termination of the employment contracts for up to two months. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 90. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 90. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vituse maksmine t&ouml;&ouml;tajale </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of compensation to employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel h&uuml;vitust: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers are required to pay the following compensation to employees upon termination of their employment contracts: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni likvideerimise (paragrahvi 86 punkt 1), t&ouml;&ouml;andja pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamise (paragrahvi 86 punkt 2), t&ouml;&ouml;tajate koondamise (paragrahvi 86 punkt 3) ja vanuse (paragrahvi 86 punkt 10) t&otilde;ttu: </eesti>
<inglise>1) due to the liquidation of the enterprise, agency or other organisation (clause 86 1)), declaration of bankruptcy of the employer (clause 86 2)), lay-off of employees (clause 86 3)) or age (clause 86 10)): </inglise>
<eesti>a) t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kellel on pidevat t&ouml;&ouml;staa&zcaron;i selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures kuni 5 aastat - kahe kuu keskmise palga ulatuses; </eesti>
<inglise>a) compensation in the amount of two months' average wages to employees who have been continuously employed by the employer for up to five years; </inglise>
<eesti>b) t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kellel on pidevat t&ouml;&ouml;staa&zcaron;i selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures 5 - 10 aastat - kolme kuu keskmise palga ulatuses; </eesti>
<inglise>b) compensation in the amount of three months' average wages to employees who have been continuously employed by the employer for five to ten years; </inglise>
<eesti>c) t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kellel on pidevat t&ouml;&ouml;staa&zcaron;i selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures &uuml;le 10 aasta - nelja kuu keskmise palga ulatuses; </eesti>
<inglise>c) compensation in the amount of four months' average wages to employees who have been continuously employed by the employer for more than ten years; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;taja mittevastavuse t&otilde;ttu (paragrahvi 86 punkt 4) - t&ouml;&ouml;taja &uuml;he kuu keskmise palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>2) due to the unsuitability of the employees (clause 86 4)), compensation in the amount of one month's average wages of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.12.96 j&otilde;ust.01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.12.96 entered into force 01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andjal puuduvad vahendid h&uuml;vituse maksmiseks t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamise t&otilde;ttu (paragrahv 86 punkt 2), maksab t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vituse riik 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud ulatuses, kuid mitte &uuml;le pankrotiseaduses s&auml;testatud ulatuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employer lacks the means to pay compensation upon termination of employment contracts due to the declaration of bankruptcy (clause 86 2)), the state shall pay compensation to the employees in the amount specified in subsection (1), but not in excess of the amount prescribed in the Bankruptcy Act. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vituse maksmise korra ja tingimused kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for and conditions of payment of compensation shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.12.96 j&otilde;ust.01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.12.96 entered into force 01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel muudel paragrahvis 86 etten&auml;htud alustel t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitust ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Compensation is not paid to employees upon termination of their employment contracts on other bases prescribed in &sect; 86. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 91. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 91. </inglise>
<eesti>Keeld l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingut t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition against termination of employment contract on initiative of employer </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel ei ole lubatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Termination of an employment contract is prohibited on the initiative of an employer: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;taja ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ajal (v&auml;lja arvatud paragrahvi 86 punkt 9); </eesti>
<inglise>1) during the temporary incapacity for work of the employee (except clause 86 9)); </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;taja puhkusel (sealhulgas lapsehooldus- ja palgata puhkusel) viibimise ajal ning perioodil, mille kestel t&ouml;&ouml;tajale oli kehtestatud osaline t&ouml;&ouml;aeg v&otilde;i ta oli saadetud osaliselt tasustatavale puhkusele paragrahv 68 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud korras; </eesti>
<inglise>2) while the employee is on a holiday (including parental leave and holidays without pay) and during periods when part-time working time has been established for the employee or he or she has been sent on a holiday with partial pay pursuant to the procedure prescribed in subsection 68 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>3) seadusliku streigi ajal, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja osaleb selles streigis seadusega etten&auml;htud korras; </eesti>
<inglise>3) during a legal strike if the employee participates in such strike pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ajal, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&auml;idab talle riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsusorgani poolt pandud &uuml;lesandeid v&otilde;i esindab seaduse v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga etten&auml;htud korras t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid. </eesti>
<inglise>4) at a time when the employee is performing duties imposed on him or her by a state or local government authority, or is representing employees pursuant to the procedure provided by law or a collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.02.93 j&otilde;ust.12.03.93 - RT 1993, 10, 150) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.02.93 entered into force 12.03.93 - RT I 1993, 10, 150) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;iget ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni likvideerimise ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Subsection (1) of this section is not applied upon termination of employment contract due to liquidation of an undertaking, agency or other organisation, or upon declaration of bankruptcy of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.12.96 j&otilde;ust.01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.12.96 entered into force 01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 92. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 92. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine raseda v&otilde;i naisega, kes kasvatab alla kolmeaastast last </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract with pregnant woman or woman raising child under three years of age </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on keelatud l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping raseda v&otilde;i naisega, kes kasvatab alla kolmeaastast last, v&auml;lja arvatud paragrahvi 86 punktides 1-2, 5-8 ja 11 etten&auml;htud alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) It is prohibited for an employer to terminate an employment contract with a pregnant woman or a woman raising a child under three years of age, except on the bases prescribed in clauses 86 1) -2), 5) -8) and 11). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes mainitud t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega paragrahvi 86 punktides 1-2 ja 5-8 etten&auml;htud alustel on lubatud &uuml;ksnes t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Termination of employment contracts with the employees specified in subsection (1) of this section on the bases prescribed in clauses 86 1) -2) and 5) -8) is only permitted with the consent of the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 93. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 93. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine alaealisega </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract with minor </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada alaealisega t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvis 86 etten&auml;htud alustel, v&auml;lja arvatud paragrahvi 86 punkt 5. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer has the right to terminate an employment contract with a minor on the grounds prescribed in &sect; 86, except for clause 86 5). </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine paragrahvi 86 punktides 3-4 etten&auml;htud alustel on lubatud &uuml;ksnes t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of an employment contract on the grounds prescribed in clauses 86 3) -4) is permitted only with the consent of the labour inspector of the seat (residence) of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 94. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 94. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajatega </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contracts with representatives of employees </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga, kes on valitud t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindavasse organisatsiooni, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindava isikuga, on lubatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja volituste ajal ja &uuml;he aasta jooksul p&auml;rast volituste l&otilde;petamist, v&auml;lja arvatud paragrahvi 86 punktides 1, 9 ja 11 etten&auml;htud alused, &uuml;ksnes t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Termination of an employment contract on the initiative of an employer with an employee who is elected to an organisation which represents employees at the workplace of the employer, or with a person who represents employees is permitted during the term of authority of the employee and for within one year after termination of the authorisation only with the consent of the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer, except on the bases prescribed in clauses 86 1), 9) and 11). </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektor peab t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kirjalikult p&otilde;hjendama t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajaga t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamiseks n&otilde;usoleku andmist v&otilde;i sellest keeldumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A labour inspector shall justify to an employer in writing the reasons for granting or refusing to grant consent to the termination of an employment contract with a representative of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>Enne vastava otsuse tegemist peab t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor p&ouml;&ouml;rduma kirjalikult t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindava organisatsiooni poole arvamuse saamiseks t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajaga t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise kohta, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindaja on t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindava organisatsiooni poolt valitud. </eesti>
<inglise>Before making the corresponding decision, the labour inspector shall submit a written request to an organisation representing employees in order to obtain an opinion concerning the termination of the employment contract with the representative of employees, if such representative has been elected by the organisation representing employees. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindav organisatsioon annab oma kirjaliku arvamuse &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>The organisation representing employees shall provide a written opinion within one week as of the date of the request. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Keelatud on t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajaga t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine tulenevalt tema seaduslikust tegevusest t&ouml;&ouml;tajate huvide esindamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) It is prohibited to terminate an employment contract with a representative of employees as a result of his or her lawful activities in representing the interests of the employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ebaseadusliku tegevuse peale saab esitada kaebuse halduskohtule. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A complaint against the unlawful activities of a labour inspector may be submitted to an administrative court. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 95. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 95. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine kohakaaslasega (2) </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract with person in second job (4) </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel kohakaaslasega ei rakendata paragrahvides 87-94 etten&auml;htud tagatisi. </eesti>
<inglise>The guarantees prescribed in &sect;&sect; 87-94 do not apply upon termination of an employment contract with a person in a second job. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 96. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 96. </inglise>
<eesti>Erisoodustuste korras saadu tagastamine t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Return of that which was acquired by way of special benefits upon termination of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu (paragrahvi 27 2. l&otilde;ike punkt 5) l&otilde;petamisel paragrahvi 86 punktides 4-8 ja paragrahvis 112 etten&auml;htud alustel, samuti niisuguse lepingu l&otilde;petamisel paragrahvis 113 etten&auml;htud alusel t&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;l, on t&ouml;&ouml;andjal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;tajalt t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel saadud erisoodustuste (t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt makstud stipendium ja kantud muud &otilde;ppekulud, &otilde;ppeajaks s&auml;ilitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tasu jms.) tagastamist. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon termination of an employment contract entered into for a specified term (clause 27 (2) 5)) on the bases prescribed in clauses 86 4) -8) and &sect; 112, and upon termination of such contract on the basis prescribed in &sect; 113 by the fault of the employee, the employer has the right to demand return of special benefits acquired on the basis of the employment contract (grants paid and other educational expenses borne by the employer, remuneration which was continued during studies, etc.). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 97. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 97. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni likvideerimisel v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon liquidation of enterprise, agency or other organisation or declaration of bankruptcy of employer </inglise>
<eesti>(18.12.96 j&otilde;ust.01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.12.96 entered into force 01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvi 86 punktis 1 etten&auml;htud alustel, kui ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni tegevus l&otilde;petatakse t&auml;ielikult ning selle baasil ei moodustata uut ettev&otilde;tet, asutust v&otilde;i muud organisatsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer has the right to terminate employment contracts with employees on the bases prescribed in clause 86 1) if the activity of the enterprise, agency or other organisation is completely terminated and no new enterprise, agency or other organisation is formed on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamisel on pankrotihalduril &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega paragrahv 86 punktis 2 etten&auml;htud alusel p&auml;rast pankrotiotsuse tegemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the declaration of bankruptcy of an employer, the trustee in bankruptcy has the right to terminate employment contracts with the employees on the basis prescribed in clause 86 2) after the bankruptcy order is issued. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.12.96 j&otilde;ust.01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.12.96 entered into force 01.02.97 - RT I 1997, 5, 32) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 98. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 98. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;tajate koondamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon lay-off of employees </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvi 86 punktis 3 etten&auml;htud alusel t&ouml;&ouml;mahu v&auml;henemisel, tootmise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; &uuml;mberkorraldamisel, varem t&ouml;&ouml;tanud t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le ennistamisel ja muudel juhtudel, mis tingivad t&ouml;&ouml; l&otilde;ppemise. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer has the right to terminate employment contracts on the basis prescribed in clause 86 3) upon a decrease in work volume, reorganisation of production or work, reinstatement of an employee in a previous position and in other cases which require termination of the work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamist koondamise t&otilde;ttu on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud pakkuma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;imaluse korral teist t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Prior to termination of an employment contract due to a lay-off, the employer is required to offer another position to the employee if possible. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud koondamise t&otilde;ttu vabanenud t&ouml;&ouml;taja tema soovil t&ouml;&ouml;le tagasi v&otilde;tma kuue kuu jooksul, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andjal tekib vabu t&ouml;&ouml;kohti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer is required to re-employ an employee who has been released due to a lay-off within six months if the employee so desires, if the employer has vacant positions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 99. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 99. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lej&auml;&auml;mise eelis&otilde;igus koondamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Preferential right to remain at work upon lay-off </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel koondamise t&otilde;ttu on t&ouml;&ouml;lej&auml;&auml;mise eelis&otilde;igus eelk&otilde;ige t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajal, seej&auml;rel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures p&otilde;hikohaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the termination of employment contracts due to lay-offs, the representatives of employees have a preferential right to remain at work, followed by the employees who work for such employer as their principal job. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&otilde;hikohaga t&ouml;&ouml;tavatest isikutest eelistatakse neid, kel on paremad t&ouml;&ouml;alased n&auml;itajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Of the persons who are employed in a principal job, preference is given to those who have better performance results. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&otilde;rdsete t&ouml;&ouml;alaste n&auml;itajate korral eelistatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid, kes on selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja s&uuml;&uuml;l saanud kutsehaiguse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;vigastuse; kes on kauem t&ouml;&ouml;tanud selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures; kellel on &uuml;lalpeetavaid; kes t&auml;iendavad oma kutseoskusi ja teadmisi eriharidust andvas &otilde;ppeasutuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case of equal performance results, preference is given to employees who have contracted an occupational disease or received a work injury by the fault of the employer; who have worked for the employer longer; who have dependants; or who are developing their professional skills and expertise in an educational institution which provides special education. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 100. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 100. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i organisatsiooni reorganiseerimisel, sealhulgas tema struktuuri&uuml;ksuse likvideerimisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contracts upon reorganisation of enterprise, agency or organisation, including liquidation of structural unit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni reorganiseerimisel l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu paragrahvi 86 punktis 3 etten&auml;htud alusel, kui reorganiseerimisega kaasneb t&ouml;&ouml;tajate koondamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the reorganisation of an enterprise, agency or other organisation, the employer has the right to terminate employment contracts on the basis prescribed in clause 86 3) if the reorganisation results in a lay-off of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni t&ouml;&ouml;andja &otilde;igusteta struktuuri&uuml;ksuse likvideerimisel l&otilde;petada seal t&ouml;&ouml;tavate t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvi 86 punktis 3 etten&auml;htud alusel, kui neile ei ole v&otilde;imalik pakkuda t&ouml;&ouml;d teises struktuuri&uuml;ksuses v&otilde;i nad on keeldunud pakutud t&ouml;&ouml;st. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the liquidation of a structural unit of an enterprise, agency or organisation which has no employment authority, the employer has the right to terminate the employment contracts of the employees who work there, on the basis prescribed in clause 86 3), if it is not possible to offer them a position in another structural unit or if they refuse an offered position. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 101. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 101. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja mittevastavusel oma ametikohale v&otilde;i tehtavale t&ouml;&ouml;le t&ouml;&ouml;oskuse v&otilde;i tervise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon unsuitability of employee for his or her office or work to be performed due to professional skills or for reasons of health </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvi 86 punktis 4 etten&auml;htud alusel, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei tule toime oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisega ebapiisava t&ouml;&ouml;oskuse v&otilde;i tervise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer has the right to terminate an employment contract on the basis prescribed in clause 86 4) if the employee cannot manage to perform his or her duties due to insufficient professional skills or for reasons of health. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu samal alusel l&otilde;petada ka siis, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>An employer may terminate an employment contract on the same basis if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;tajal puudus dokument, mille olemasolu on vastavale t&ouml;&ouml;le lubamise kohustuslik eeltingimus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the employee lacks a document which is a mandatory precondition for such work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei vasta oma t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;i ametikohale ebapiisava keele- v&otilde;i suhtlemisoskuse t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the employee is unsuitable for his or her position or office due to insufficient language or communication skills; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei t&auml;ienda erialaseid teadmisi (sealhulgas riigikeele ja v&otilde;&otilde;rkeelte oskust), kui see on t&ouml;&ouml;ks vajalik ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja on talle selleks tingimused loonud vastavalt kokkulepitud korrale. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the employee fails to develop his or her professional knowledge (including proficiency in the official language and foreign languages) if this is necessary for the performance of his or her work and if the employer has provided the employee with the opportunity therefor pursuant to the agreed procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 327) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja tervise halvenemine v&otilde;ib olla t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&otilde;hjuseks, kui see on p&uuml;siva iseloomuga ja takistab senise t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamist v&otilde;i v&auml;listab senise t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The deterioration of the health of an employee may be the reason for the termination of his or her employment contract if it is of a continuous nature and hinders or precludes continuation in his or her current position. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja kutseoskuse vastavust t&auml;idetavale ametikohale v&otilde;i tehtavale t&ouml;&ouml;le hindab t&ouml;&ouml;andja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer evaluates the conformity of the professional skills of the employee to the office to be held or the position to be filled. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja tervise vastavus m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks arsti otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The conformity of the health of the employee is determined by the decision of a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib l&otilde;petada paragrahvi 86 punktis 4 etten&auml;htud alusel t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ei ole v&otilde;imalik pakkuda teist t&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;i kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on keeldunud pakutud t&ouml;&ouml;st. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employer may terminate an employment contract on the basis prescribed in clause 86 4) if it is not possible to offer another position to the employee or if the employee refuses an offered position. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 102. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 102. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine katseaja ebarahuldavate tulemuste t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract due to unsatisfactory results of probationary period </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada paragrahvi 86 punktis 5 etten&auml;htud alusel t&ouml;&ouml;leping, kui katseaja tulemused osutuvad ebarahuldavaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer has the right to terminate an employment contract on the basis prescribed in clause 86 5) if the results of the probationary period prove unsatisfactory. </inglise>
<eesti>Katseaja tulemusi hindab t&ouml;&ouml;andja. </eesti>
<inglise>The results of the probationary period are evaluated by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petada katseaja kestel (kaasa arvatud katseaja viimane p&auml;ev). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer may terminate an employment contract during a probationary period (including on the last day of the probationary period). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 103. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 103. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;tajapoolsel t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste rikkumisel v&otilde;i korruptiivse teo toimepanemisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon breach of duties or commitment of act of corruption by employee </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada paragrahvi 86 punktis 6 etten&auml;htud alusel t&ouml;&ouml;leping, kui s&uuml;&uuml;tegu h&auml;iris t&ouml;&ouml;d ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajal on distsiplinaarkaristus, mis ei ole kustunud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer has the right to terminate an employment contract on the basis prescribed in clause 86 6) if a wrongful act impeded the work and the employee is subject to a disciplinary punishment which has not expired. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petada ka t&ouml;&ouml;taja esmakordse j&auml;meda t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste rikkumise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer may terminate an employment contract for the first severe breach of duties by an employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 86 punktis 12 etten&auml;htud alusel iga t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga, kes paneb toime korruptiivse teo. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer has the right to terminate an employment contract with each employee who commits an act of corruption on the basis prescribed in clause 86 12) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 104. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 104. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja suhtes usalduse kaotamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon loss of trust in employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvi 86 punktis 7 etten&auml;htud alusel iga t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga, kelle suhtes t&ouml;&ouml;andja on kaotanud usalduse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer has the right to terminate an employment contract on the basis prescribed in clause 86 7) with any employee in whom the employer loses trust. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;ib l&otilde;petada, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employment contract may be terminated if an employee has: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&otilde;hjustanud t&ouml;&ouml;andja vara puuduj&auml;&auml;gi, riknemise, h&auml;vimise, kaotsimineku v&otilde;i riisumise, samuti kui ta on t&ouml;&ouml;kohal varastanud kaast&ouml;&ouml;taja vara; </eesti>
<inglise>1) caused a deficit in, damage to, or destruction, loss or theft of the property of the employer, or if he or she has stolen the property of a co-worker at the workplace; </inglise>
<eesti>2) seadnud ohtu t&ouml;&ouml;andja vara s&auml;ilimise; </eesti>
<inglise>2) endangered the preservation of the property of the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&otilde;hjustanud tarbijate, klientide v&otilde;i &auml;ripartnerite usaldamatuse t&ouml;&ouml;andja vastu; </eesti>
<inglise>3) caused distrust of the employer by consumers, clients or business partners. </inglise>
<eesti>4) (Kehtetu - 27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>4) (Repealed - 27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>5) (Kehtetu - 27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>5) (Repealed - 27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>6) (Kehtetu - 27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>6) (Repealed - 27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>7) (Kehtetu - 27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>7) (Repealed - 27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 105. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 105. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine v&auml;&auml;ritu teo eest </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract for indecent act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvi 86 punktis 8 etten&auml;htud alusel pedagoogide, alaealiste juhendajate ja muude t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeks on noori &otilde;petada v&otilde;i kasvatada, samuti riigi ja kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutuse abiteenistujatega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers have the right to terminate employment contracts on the basis prescribed in clause 86 8) with employees who are teachers, instructors of minors or others whose duties are to teach or educate youth, and support staff of local government administrative agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(05.05.93 j&otilde;ust.01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441; 25.01.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 16, 228) </eesti>
<inglise>05.05.93 entered into force 01.09.93 - RT I 1993, 26, 441; 25.01.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 16, 228) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;&auml;rituks on tegu, mis on vastuolus &uuml;ldtunnustatud k&otilde;lblusnormidega v&otilde;i diskrediteerib t&ouml;&ouml;tajat v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Acts which are in contrary to generally recognised moral standards or which discredit an employee or employer are indecent. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;ritu tegu on t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise aluseks ka siis, kui see pandi toime v&auml;ljaspool t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>An indecent act also constitutes the basis for termination of an employment contract if it is committed outside of the performance of duties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 106. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 106. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;tegude t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract due to wrongful act of employee </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel paragrahvi 86 punktides 6-8 etten&auml;htud alustel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud j&auml;rgima distsiplinaarkaristuste m&auml;&auml;ramiseks seadusega kehtestatud korda. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon terminating an employment contract on the bases prescribed in clauses 86 6) -8), an employer is required to adhere to the procedure prescribed by law for imposing disciplinary punishments. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja ei ole kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest t&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;tegude t&otilde;ttu ette teatama ega h&uuml;vitust maksma. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer is not required to notify an employee in advance of the termination of his or her employment contract due to a wrongful act of the employee or to pay compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 107. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 107. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine pikaajalise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract due to long-term incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvi 86 punktis 9 etten&auml;htud alusel t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ajal: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer has the right to terminate an employment contract on the basis prescribed in clause 86 9) during time that an employee is incapacitated for work: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu t&ouml;&ouml;lt puudunud &uuml;le nelja kuu j&auml;rjest, tuberkuloosi haigestumise t&otilde;ttu &uuml;le kaheksa kuu j&auml;rjest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) if the employee has been absent from work due to incapacity for work for more than four consecutive months; if, due to contraction of tuberculosis the employee has been absent from work for more than eight consecutive months; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu t&ouml;&ouml;lt puudunud &uuml;le viie kuu kalendriaasta jooksul, tuberkuloosi haigestumise t&otilde;ttu &uuml;le kaheksa kuu kalendriaasta jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>2) if the employee has been absent from work due to incapacity for work for more than five months during a calendar year; if, due to contraction of tuberculosis, the employee has been absent from work for more than eight months during a calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.11.07.96 - RT 1 1996, 45, 850) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 11.07.96 - RT I 1996, 45, 850) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;vigastuse t&otilde;ttu ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks j&auml;&auml;nule s&auml;ilitab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;koha tema tervenemiseni v&otilde;i invaliidsuse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer shall maintain the job of an employee who is temporarily incapacitated for work due to a work injury until his or her recovery or determination of his or her disability. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ajal on t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise p&auml;evaks t&ouml;&ouml;lepingusse kande tegemise p&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The date of termination of an employment contract during an employee's incapacity for work is the date that such entry is made in the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 108. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 108. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja vanuse t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract due to age of employee </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;leping paragrahvi 86 punktis 10 etten&auml;htud alusel, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on saanud 65 aastaseks ja tal on &otilde;igus t&auml;isvanaduspensionile. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer has the right to terminate the employment contract of an employee on the basis prescribed in clause 86 10) if the employee has attained sixty-five years of age and he or she has the right to receive full old-age pension. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 109. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 109. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine p&otilde;hikohaga t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmisel (3) </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon hiring employee for whom job is principal job (5) </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib l&otilde;petada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kohakaaslasega paragrahvi 86 punktis 11 etten&auml;htud alusel, kui kohakaaslase asemele v&otilde;etakse p&otilde;hikohaga t&ouml;&ouml;taja. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer may terminate an employment contract with a person in a second job on the basis prescribed in clause 86 11) if an employee for whom the position is a principal job replaces the person for whom it is a second job. </inglise>
<eesti>5. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 5 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine kolmandate isikute n&otilde;udmisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of Employment Contracts at Request of Third Parties </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 110. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 110. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine alaealisega kolmandate isikute n&otilde;udmisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contracts with minors at request of third parties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Alaealise vanem, eestkostja, hooldaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor v&otilde;ivad n&otilde;uda alaealisega s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamist, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tamine ohustab alaealise tervist, k&otilde;lblust v&otilde;i hariduse omandamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The parent, guardian, curator or the labour inspector of the location (residence) of an employer may demand termination of an employment contract entered into with a minor if the work endangers the health, morality or education of the minor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud alusel l&otilde;petab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu vastava kirjaliku n&otilde;ude esitamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) On the basis prescribed in subsection (1) of this section, an employer terminates an employment contract on the date following the date of submission of the corresponding written demand. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud maksma alaealisele t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel h&uuml;vitust tema &uuml;he kuu keskmise palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon termination of the employment contract of a minor, the employer is required to pay compensation to the minor in the amount of his or her average one month's wages. </inglise>
<eesti>6. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 6 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine pooltest s&otilde;ltumatutel asjaoludel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of Employment Contract in Circumstances Independent of Parties </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 111. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 111. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine kaitsej&otilde;udude tegevteenistusse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;teenistusse kutsumisel v&otilde;i astumisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon conscription or entry into active service in armed forces or alternative service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja l&otilde;petab t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&ouml;&ouml;taja kaitsej&otilde;udude tegevteenistusse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;teenistusse kutsumisel v&otilde;i astumisel v&auml;hemalt kolm kalendrip&auml;eva enne vastaval kutsel m&auml;rgitud t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer terminates the employment contract of an employee upon conscription or entry of the employee into active service in the armed forces or alternative service at least three calendar days prior to the date designated in the corresponding notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatada t&ouml;&ouml;taja kaitsej&otilde;udude tegevteenistuses v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;teenistuses viibimise ajaks (paragrahvi 55 punkt 7). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) By agreement of the parties, the employment contract of an employee may be suspended for the duration of the time that the employee is in active service in the armed forces or alternative service (clause 55 7)). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel t&ouml;&ouml;taja kutsumisel v&otilde;i asumisel kaitsej&otilde;udude tegevteenistusse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;teenistusse maksab riik t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitusena tema kahe n&auml;dala keskmise palga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon termination of the employment contract of an employee upon conscription or commencement of active service in the armed forces or alternative service, the state shall pay the employee's two weeks' average wages to the employee as compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vituse maksmise korra kehtestab vabariigi valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for payment of compensation shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 112. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 112. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon entry into force of conviction by court </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petatakse s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumisel, millega t&ouml;&ouml;tajale m&otilde;isteti kriminaalkaristus, mis teeb v&otilde;imatuks senise t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment contract is terminated upon the entry into force of a conviction by a court which imposes a criminal punishment on an employee which makes it impossible for him or her to continue his or her current employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja vahi alla v&otilde;tmisel l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;leping p&auml;rast s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumist vahi alla v&otilde;tmise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employee is taken into custody, his or her employment contract is terminated after the entry into force of a conviction by a court as of the date on which the employee is taken into custody. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 113. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 113. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmise eeskirjade rikkumisel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract upon violation of rules for hiring </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmise eeskirjade rikkumise t&otilde;ttu, kui leping s&otilde;lmiti paragrahvide 32, 35, 36 ja 37 3. l&otilde;ike rikkumisega. (4) </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment contract is terminated due to violation of the rules for hiring if the contract was entered into in violation of &sect;&sect; 32, 35, 36 or subsection 37 (3). (6) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmiti t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmise eeskirjade rikkumisega t&ouml;&ouml;andja s&uuml;&uuml;l, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud pakkuma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale teist t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employment contract is entered into in violation of the rules for hiring by the fault of the employer, the employer is required to offer other work to the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja s&uuml;&uuml;l t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmise eeskirjade rikkumisega s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitust tema kolme kuu keskmise palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon termination of an employment contract entered into in violation of the rules for hiring by the fault of an employer, the employer is required to pay compensation to the employee in the amount of his or her average three months' wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmiti t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmise eeskirjade rikkumisega t&ouml;&ouml;taja poolt teadlikult eba&otilde;igete andmete esitamise tagaj&auml;rjel, on t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;andjale h&uuml;vitust oma &uuml;he kuu keskmise palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an employment contract is entered into in violation of the rules for hiring as a result of knowingly incorrect information provided by the employee, the employee is required to pay compensation to the employer in the amount of the employee's one month's average wages. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 114. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 114. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine l&auml;hedase sugulase v&otilde;i h&otilde;imlasega </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract with close relative or relative by marriage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petatakse &uuml;hega l&auml;hedases suguluses v&otilde;i h&otilde;imluses olevatest t&ouml;&ouml;tajatest (paragrahv 32), kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad &uuml;hes ja samas riiklikus v&otilde;i munitsipaalettev&otilde;ttes, asutuses v&otilde;i muus organisatsioonis &uuml;ksteise vahetus alluvuses oleval v&otilde;i teise poolt vahetult kontrollitaval ametikohal, kui selline t&ouml;&ouml;tamine pole lubatud seaduse v&otilde;i vabariigi valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment contract is terminated with one of the employees who are closely related or are related by marriage (&sect; 32) who work in the same state or municipal enterprise, agency or other organisation in positions which are directly subordinate to or have direct control over the other, unless such work is allowed by an Act or regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud alusel pakub t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;imalusel t&ouml;&ouml;tajale teist t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon termination of an employment contract on the basis prescribed in subsection (1) of this section, the employer shall offer the employee another position if possible. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 115. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 115. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja surma t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract due to death of employee </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja surma korral l&otilde;petab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&ouml;&ouml;taja surmap&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the death of an employee, the employer terminates his or her employment contract as of the date of death. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 116. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 116. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;andja surma t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment contract due to death of employer </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja surm ei l&otilde;peta t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtivust, v&auml;lja arvatud, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;etud t&ouml;&ouml;andja isiklikuks teenindamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The death of an employer does not terminate the validity of an employment contract, except if the employee was hired for the provision of personal services to the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul l&otilde;petavad t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&ouml;&ouml;andja p&auml;rijad v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) j&auml;rgne t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the successors of the employer or the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer terminate the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja surmap&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>The employment contract is terminated as of the date of death of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>7. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte vastutus t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu ebaseaduslikul l&otilde;petamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of Parties upon Illegal Termination of Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 117. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 117. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja vastutus t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu ebaseaduslikul l&otilde;petamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of employer upon illegal termination of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu ebaseaduslikul l&otilde;petamisel t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda enda t&ouml;&ouml;le ennistamist, t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise aluse formuleeringu muutmist ja sunnitud t&ouml;&ouml;lt puudumise aja eest keskmise palga maksmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon illegal termination of an employment contract by an employer, the employee has the right to demand reinstatement in his or her position, amendment of the statement of the basis for termination of the employment contract and payment of his or her average wages for the time of compelled absence from work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja loobub t&ouml;&ouml;le ennistamisest, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitust kuni t&ouml;&ouml;taja kuue kuu keskmise palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employee waives reinstatement in his or her position, the employer is required to pay compensation to the employee in the amount of his or her six months' average wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindaja loobub t&ouml;&ouml;le ennistamisest, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud maksma h&uuml;vitust tema kuue kuu keskmise palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a representative of employees waives reinstatement in his or her position, the employer is required to pay compensation to the representative in the amount of his or her six months' average wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 118. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 118. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja vastutus omavolilisel t&ouml;&ouml;lt lahkumisel </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of employee for ceasing employment without authorisation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja lahkub t&ouml;&ouml;lt omavoliliselt t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise kohta avaldust esitamata (paragrahvid 79 ja 80), on t&ouml;&ouml;andjal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;tajalt h&uuml;vitust kuni tema &uuml;he kuu keskmise palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an employee ceases employment without authorisation and does not give notice of termination of the employment contract (&sect;&sect; 79 and 80), the employer has the right to demand compensation from the employee in the amount of his or her one month's average wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes oli s&otilde;lminud m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks erisoodustustega t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu (paragrahvi 27 2. l&otilde;ike punkt 5), lahkub t&ouml;&ouml;lt omavoliliselt, on t&ouml;&ouml;andjal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;tajalt lisaks t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel saadu tagastamisele (paragrahv 96) h&uuml;vitust kuni tema kolme kuu keskmise palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employee who has entered into an employment contract for a specified term with special benefits (clause 27 (2) 5)) ceases employment without authorisation, the employer has the right to demand compensation from the employee in the amount of the employee's three months' average wages in addition to the return of that which was received under the employment contract (&sect; 96). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 119. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 119. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu ja l&otilde;pparve kinnipidamise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability for withholding employment record book and final settlement </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;raamatu kinnipidamisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale keskmist palka iga t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu k&auml;tteandmisega viivitatud p&auml;eva eest kuni t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu k&auml;tteandmiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon withholding an employment record book, an employer is required to pay the employee his or her average wages for each day of delay in delivery of the employment record book until the employment record book has been delivered. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;pparve kinnipidamisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale keskmist palka iga l&otilde;pparve v&auml;ljamaksmisega viivitamise p&auml;eva eest, kuid mitte &uuml;le t&ouml;&ouml;taja &uuml;he kuu keskmise palga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon withholding a final settlement, an employer is required to pay the employee his or her average wages for each day of delay in payment of the final settlement, but not more than one month's average wages of the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamine ja kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Cancellation and Declaration of Invalidity of Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamine </eesti>
<inglise>Cancellation of Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 120. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 120. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for cancellation of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;ib enne t&ouml;&ouml;le asumist t&uuml;histada poolte kokkuleppel, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel. </eesti>
<inglise>An employment contract may be terminated prior to commencement of employment by agreement of the parties, or on the initiative of the employee or the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 121. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 121. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamine poolte kokkuleppel </eesti>
<inglise>Cancellation of employment contract by agreement of parties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histada mis tahes p&otilde;hjusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) By agreement of the parties, an employment contract may be cancelled for any reason. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andjalt lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu tagastamine otsustatakse poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The return of that which was received from an employer under an employment contract is decided by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 122. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 122. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja algatusel </eesti>
<inglise>Cancellation of employment contract on initiative of employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;ib t&uuml;histada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu, kui t&ouml;&ouml;le asumine on takistatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee may cancel his or her employment contract if commencement of employment is hindered: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tema ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) due to his or her temporary incapacity for work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ootamatute perekondlike v&otilde;i ootamatute isiklike p&otilde;hjuste t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) due to unexpected family or personal reasons; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tema kaitsej&otilde;udude tegevteenistusse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;teenistusse kutsumise v&otilde;i astumise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>3) due to his or her conscription or entry into active service in the armed forces or alternative service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamisel tagastab t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kogu lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon cancellation of an employment contract the employee shall return to the employer all that was received under the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 123. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 123. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamine t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel </eesti>
<inglise>Cancellation of employment contract on initiative of employer </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib t&uuml;histada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer may cancel an employment contract if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei asu lepitud ajaks t&ouml;&ouml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the employee does not commence employment at the agreed time; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;andja (paragrahvi 3 punkt 3) kutsutakse v&otilde;i astub kaitsej&otilde;udude tegevteenistusse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;teenistusse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the employer (clause 3 3)) is conscripted or enters into active service in the armed forces or alternative service; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;andja (paragrahvi 3 punkt 3) on v&otilde;etud vahi alla; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the employer (clause 3 3)) is taken into custody; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;andja (paragrahvi 3 punkt 3) suhtes on j&otilde;ustunud s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istev kohtuotsus, millega talle m&otilde;isteti kriminaalkaristus, mis teeb v&otilde;imatuks t&ouml;&ouml;andjana tegutsemise. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a conviction of a court has entered into force regarding the employer (clause 3 3)), by which a criminal punishment was imposed on the employer which makes it impossible for the employer to act as an employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingut ei t&uuml;histata k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel, kui pooled s&otilde;lmivad t&ouml;&ouml;le asumise kohta uue kokkuleppe. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employment contract is not cancelled pursuant to subsection (1) of this section if the parties enter into a new agreement regarding commencement of unemployment. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamisel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 1 alusel tagastab t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kogu lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon cancellation of an employment contract pursuant to clause (1) 1) of this section, the employee shall return to the employer all that was received under the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Peale selle maksab t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes j&auml;ttis t&ouml;&ouml;andjale m&otilde;juva p&otilde;hjuseta teatamata, et ta ei asu lepitud ajaks t&ouml;&ouml;le, t&ouml;&ouml;andjale h&uuml;vitusena oma kahe n&auml;dala kokkulepitud palga. </eesti>
<inglise>In addition, an employee who, without good reason, fails to notify the employer that he or she will not commence employment at the agreed time shall pay compensation to the employer in the amount of the employee's two week's agreed wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamisel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 2 alusel otsustatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu tagastamine poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon cancellation of an employment contract pursuant to clause (1) 2) of this section, the return of that which was received from the employer under the contract is decided by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vituse maksmist reguleerib eriseadus. </eesti>
<inglise>The payment of compensation to employees shall be regulated by a specific Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamisel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 3 ja 4 etten&auml;htud alustel maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitusena tema &uuml;he kuu kokkulepitud palga. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon cancellation of an employment contract on the bases prescribed in clauses (1) 3) and 4) of this section, the employer shall pay compensation to the employee in the amount of his or her one month's agreed wages. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 124. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 124. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalisation of cancellation of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamise kohta teeb t&ouml;&ouml;andja lepingusse kande, milles n&auml;idatakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamise aluse formuleering viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile, t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;histamise p&auml;ev, t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjale h&uuml;vituse maksmine ja lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu tagastamine. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer shall make an entry in a contract regarding the cancellation of the employment contract with a statement of the basis for cancellation of the employment contract and reference to the section, subsection and clause of this Act, the date of cancellation of the employment contract, the payment of compensation to the employee or employer and return of that which was received under the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Declaration of Invalidity of Employment Contract </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 125. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 125. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for declaration of invalidity of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;vaidlusorgan tunnistab kehtetuks t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A labour dispute resolution body shall declare an employment contract invalid: </inglise>
<eesti>1) mille m&otilde;lemad pooled olid alaealised v&otilde;i vaimuhaiguse v&otilde;i n&otilde;rgam&otilde;istuslikkuse tagaj&auml;rjel teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isikud - &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik kumma poole eestkostja (hooldaja) hagi p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>1) if both parties were minors or persons divested of active legal capacity as a consequence of an unsound mind or mental disability, on the basis of an action by the guardian (curator) of either party; </inglise>
<eesti>2) mille t&ouml;&ouml;andjana s&otilde;lmis vaimuhaiguse v&otilde;i n&otilde;rgam&otilde;istuslikkuse tagaj&auml;rjel teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isik - niisuguse isiku eestkostja hagi p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>2) which was entered into in the capacity of employer by a person divested of active legal capacity as a consequence of an unsound mind or mental disability, on the basis of an action by the guardian of such person; </inglise>
<eesti>3) mille t&ouml;&ouml;andjana s&otilde;lmis alaealine - niisuguse alaealise &uuml;he vanema v&otilde;i eestkostja (hooldaja) hagi p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>3) which was entered into in the capacity of employer by a minor, on the basis of an action by one parent or the guardian (curator) of such minor; </inglise>
<eesti>4) mille t&ouml;&ouml;tajana s&otilde;lmis 13-18-aastane alaealine ilma &uuml;he vanema, eestkostja, hooldaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekuta v&otilde;i alla 13-aastane alaealine - niisuguse alaealise &uuml;he vanema, eestkostja, hooldaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori hagi p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>4) which was entered into in the capacity of employee by a minor of thirteen to eighteen years of age without the consent of one parent, a guardian, curator or the labour inspector, or by a minor under thirteen years of age, on the basis of an action by one parent, the guardian or curator of such minor or the labour inspector; </inglise>
<eesti>5) mille t&ouml;&ouml;tajana s&otilde;lmis vaimuhaige v&otilde;i n&otilde;rgam&otilde;istuslikkuse tagaj&auml;rjel teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isik - niisuguse isiku eestkostja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori hagi p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>5) which was entered into in the capacity of employee by a person of unsound mind or a person divested of active legal capacity as a consequence of a mental disability, on the basis of an action by the guardian of such person or the labour inspector; </inglise>
<eesti>6) mille t&ouml;&ouml;tajana s&otilde;lmis 15-18-aastane alaealine - niisuguse alaealise &uuml;he vanema, hooldaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori hagi p&otilde;hjal, kui t&ouml;&ouml;le asumine ohustaks alaealise tervist, k&otilde;lblust v&otilde;i hariduse omandamist; </eesti>
<inglise>6) which was entered into in the capacity of employee by a minor of fifteen to eighteen years of age, on the basis of an action by one parent or the curator of such minor or the labour inspector if commencement of employment would endanger the health, morality or education of the minor; </inglise>
<eesti>7) mille s&otilde;lmis isik, kes oli lepingu s&otilde;lmimise ajal seisundis, kus ta ei v&otilde;inud m&otilde;ista oma tegude t&auml;hendust v&otilde;i neid juhtida - niisuguse isiku hagi p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>7) which was entered into by a person who, at the time of entry into the contract, was in such a condition that he or she could not understand the meaning of or direct his or her actions, on the basis of an action by such person; </inglise>
<eesti>8) mis s&otilde;lmiti pettuse, v&auml;givalla, &auml;hvarduse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja esindaja kuritahtliku kokkuleppe m&otilde;jul t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga - kannatanu hagi p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>8) which was entered into with the employee under the influence of fraud, violence, a threat, or a malicious agreement with the representative of the employer, on the basis of an action by the victim; </inglise>
<eesti>9) mis s&otilde;lmiti olulise t&auml;htsusega eksimuse m&otilde;jul - eksimuse m&otilde;jul tegutsenud poole hagi p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>9) which was entered into under the influence of an error of essential importance, on the basis of an action by the party which acted under the influence of such error; </inglise>
<eesti>10) mille t&ouml;&ouml;andjana s&otilde;lmis alkohoolsete jookide v&otilde;i narkootiliste v&otilde;i toksiliste ainete kuritarvitamise tagaj&auml;rjel piiratult teov&otilde;imeliseks tunnistatud isik - niisuguse isiku hooldaja hagi p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>10) which was entered into in the capacity of employer by a person declared to have limited active legal capacity as a consequence of abuse of alcoholic beverages, narcotic drugs or toxic substances, on the basis of an action by the curator of such person; </inglise>
<eesti>11) mis s&otilde;lmiti, rikkudes t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja jaoks kehtestatud k&otilde;rgendatud vanusem&auml;&auml;ra (paragrahvi 2 ja paragrahvi 3 punkt 3) - &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik kumma poole hagi p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise>11) which was entered into in violation of a higher age limit established for employees or employers (&sect; 2 and clause 3 3)), on the basis of an action by either party. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;leping, mille t&ouml;&ouml;andjana s&otilde;lmis juriidilise isiku struktuuri&uuml;ksus, kellele ei ole antud t&ouml;&ouml;andja &otilde;igusi, v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja esindaja, kellel puudub t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimise &otilde;igus, j&auml;&auml;b kehtima, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja on n&otilde;us t&ouml;&ouml;suhte tekkimise v&otilde;i j&auml;tkamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employment contract which was entered into in the capacity of employer by a structural unit of a legal person which does not have employment authority, or by a representative of an employer who lacks the right to enter into employment contracts, remains valid if the employer agrees to the creation or continuation of such employment relationship. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja ei ole n&otilde;us t&ouml;&ouml;suhte tekkimise v&otilde;i j&auml;tkamisega, tunnistab ta t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise>If the employer does not agree to the creation or continuation of such employment relationship, the employer shall declare the employment contract invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 126. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 126. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumine hagi l&auml;bivaatamise ajaks </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of employment contract during hearing of action </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;leping peatub (paragrahvi 54) paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ikes mainitud hagi esitamise p&auml;evast kuni kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evani. </eesti>
<inglise>An employment contract is suspended (&sect; 54) from the date an action referred to in subsection 125 (1) is filed until the date of entry into force of the court order. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 127. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 127. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamise hetk </eesti>
<inglise>Moment of declaration of invalidity of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;leping tunnistatakse kehtetuks s&otilde;lmimise hetkest. </eesti>
<inglise>An employment contract is declared invalid as of the moment of entry into the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 128. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 128. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetust tingivate asjaolude &auml;ralangemine </eesti>
<inglise>Cessation of circumstances causing invalidity of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetust tingivate asjaolude (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punktid 1-6 ning 9 ja 11) &auml;ralangemisel, samuti paragrahvis 125 mainitud hagi rahuldamata j&auml;tmisel kehtib leping s&otilde;lmimise hetkest. </eesti>
<inglise>If circumstances causing the invalidity of an employment contract (clauses 125 (1) 1) -6), 9) and 11)) cease to exist and an action referred to in &sect; 125 is dismissed, a contract is valid from the moment of entry into the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 129. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 129. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui pooled olid alaealised v&otilde;i teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isikud </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if parties were minors or persons divested of active legal capacity </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et lepingu m&otilde;lemad pooled olid alaealised v&otilde;i vaimuhaiguse v&otilde;i n&otilde;rgam&otilde;istuslikkuse tagaj&auml;rjel teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isikud (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 1), tagastab t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kogu lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu, v&auml;lja arvatud tasu t&ouml;&ouml;andja eestkostja poolt vajalikuks peetud t&ouml;&ouml; eest, mis ei v&otilde;i olla v&auml;iksem vabariigi valitsuse poolt vastava t&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks kehtestatud palga alamm&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that both parties were minors or persons divested of active legal capacity as a consequence of an unsound mind or mental disability (clause 125 (1) 1)), the employee shall return to the employer all that was received under the contract, except remuneration for which the guardian of the employer considers necessary, which shall not be less than the minimum wage rate established by the Government of the Republic for performance of such work. </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte poolt &uuml;ksteisele tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitavad t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;iguse normide j&auml;rgi nende eestkostjad, kui nad ei t&otilde;enda, et t&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmiti mitte nende s&uuml;&uuml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>Damage caused to each other by the parties is compensated for by their guardians pursuant to the rules of labour law, unless the guardians prove that the employment contract was entered into without fault on their part. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 130. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 130. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja oli tunnistatud teov&otilde;imetuks </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if employer was divested of active legal capacity </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et t&ouml;&ouml;andja oli lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel vaimuhaiguse v&otilde;i n&otilde;rgam&otilde;istuslikkuse tagaj&auml;rjel teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isik (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 2), tagastab t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kogu lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu, v&auml;lja arvatud tasu t&ouml;&ouml;andja eestkostja poolt vajalikuks peetud t&ouml;&ouml; eest, mis ei v&otilde;i olla v&auml;iksem vabariigi valitsuse poolt vastava t&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks kehtestatud palga alamm&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the employer was divested of active legal capacity as a consequence of an unsound mind or mental disability at the time of entering into the contract (clause 125 (1) 2)), the employee shall return to the employer all that was received under the contract, except remuneration for work which the guardian of the employer considers necessary, which shall not be less than the minimum wage rate established by the Government of the Republic for performance of such work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes oli teadlik t&ouml;&ouml;andja teov&otilde;imetusest, h&uuml;vitab t&ouml;&ouml;andjale tekitatud kahju tsiviil&otilde;iguse normide j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employee who was aware of the incapacity of the employer shall compensate the employer for damage caused to the employer pursuant to the rules of civil law. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt niisugusele t&ouml;&ouml;tajale tekitatud kahju ei h&uuml;vitata. </eesti>
<inglise>Damage caused by the employer to such an employee is not compensated for. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes ei olnud teadlik t&ouml;&ouml;andja teov&otilde;imetusest, h&uuml;vitab t&ouml;&ouml;andjale tekitatud kahju t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;iguse normide j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employee who was not aware of the incapacity of the employer shall compensate the employer for damage caused to the employer pursuant to the rules of labour law. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt niisugusele t&ouml;&ouml;tajale tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitab t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;iguse normide j&auml;rgi t&ouml;&ouml;andja eestkostja, kui ta ei t&otilde;enda, et t&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmiti mitte tema s&uuml;&uuml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>Damage caused by the employer to such an employee is compensated for pursuant to the rules of labour law by the guardian of the employer unless the guardian proves that the employment contract was entered into without fault on his or her part. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 131. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 131. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja oli alaealine </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if employer was minor </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et t&ouml;&ouml;andja oli lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel alaealine (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 3), kohaldatakse paragrahvi 130 1. ja 2. l&otilde;iget. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the employer was a minor at the time of entering into the contract (clause 125 (1) 3)), subsections 130 (1) and (2) apply. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 132. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 132. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli alaealine </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if employee was minor </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel 13-18-aastane alaealine, kes s&otilde;lmis lepingu ilma &uuml;he vanema, eestkostja, hooldaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekuta, v&otilde;i alla 13-aastane alaealine (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 4), on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal k&otilde;ik t&ouml;&ouml;lepingust tulenevad &otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the employee was a minor of thirteen to eighteen years of age at the time of entering into the contract and entered into the contract without the consent of one parent, his or her guardian, curator or the labour inspector, or was a minor under thirteen years of age (clause 125 (1) 4)), the employee has all rights arising from the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Kehtetuks tunnistatud leping alaealisele t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kohustusi ei tekita. </eesti>
<inglise>A contract which has been declared invalid does not impose obligations on a minor employee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 133. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 133. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isik </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if employee was person divested of legal capacity </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et t&ouml;&ouml;tajana s&otilde;lmis t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu vaimuhaiguse v&otilde;i n&otilde;rgam&otilde;istuslikkuse tagaj&auml;rjel teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isik (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 5), on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal k&otilde;ik t&ouml;&ouml;lepingust tulenevad &otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the employment contract was entered into in the capacity of employee by a person divested of active legal capacity as a consequence of an unsound mind or mental disability (clause 125 (1) 5)), the employee has all rights arising from the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja poolt t&ouml;&ouml;andjale tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitab t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;iguse normide j&auml;rgi niisuguse t&ouml;&ouml;taja eestkostja, kui ta ei t&otilde;enda, et t&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmiti mitte tema s&uuml;&uuml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>Damage caused by an employee divested of active legal capacity to an employer is compensated for pursuant to the rules of labour law by the guardian of such employee unless the guardian proves that the employment contract was entered into without fault on his or her part. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 134. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 134. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui t&ouml;&ouml;le asumine ohustaks alaealise tervist, k&otilde;lblust v&otilde;i hariduse omandamist </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if commencement of employment would endanger health, morality or education of minor </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et t&ouml;&ouml;le asumine ohustaks 15-18-aastase alaealise tervist, k&otilde;lblust v&otilde;i hariduse omandamist (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 6), tagastab alaealine t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kogu lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that commencement of employment would endanger the health, morality or education of a minor of fifteen to eighteen years of age (clause 125 (1) 6)), the minor shall return to the employer all that was received under the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 135. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 135. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui lepingupool ei olnud v&otilde;imeline m&otilde;istma oma tegude t&auml;hendust </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if party to contract was not capable of understanding meaning of own actions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;leping tunnistati kehtetuks seet&otilde;ttu, et t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel seisundis, kus ta ei v&otilde;inud m&otilde;ista oma tegude t&auml;hendust v&otilde;i neid juhtida (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 7), on niisugusel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal k&otilde;ik t&ouml;&ouml;lepingust tulenevad &otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the employee was, at the time of entry into the contract, in such a condition that he or she could not understand the meaning of or direct his or her actions (clause 125 (1) 7)), such employee has all rights arising from the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Peale selle maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja, kes oli teadlik t&ouml;&ouml;taja niisugusest seisundist, t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitusena tema kolme kuu keskmise palga, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on t&ouml;&ouml;le asunud, ja tema kolme kuu kokkulepitud palga, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei ole veel t&ouml;&ouml;le asunud. </eesti>
<inglise>In addition, if the employer was aware of the employee's condition, the employer shall pay compensation to the employee in the amount of his or her three months' average wages if the employee has commenced employment or in the amount of his or her three months' agreed wages if the employee has not yet commenced employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;leping tunnistati kehtetuks seet&otilde;ttu, et t&ouml;&ouml;andja oli lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel seisundis, kus ta ei v&otilde;inud m&otilde;ista oma tegude t&auml;hendust v&otilde;i neid juhtida (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 7), on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;andja oli niisuguses seisundis, &otilde;igus tasule t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt vajalikuks peetud t&ouml;&ouml; eest, mis ei v&otilde;i olla v&auml;iksem vabariigi valitsuse poolt vastava t&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks kehtestatud palga alamm&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the employer was, at the time of entry into the contract, in such a condition that he or she could not understand the meaning of or direct his or her actions (clause 125 (1) 7)), an employee whose employer was in such condition has the right to receive the remuneration for work which the employer considers necessary, but which shall not be less than the minimum wage rate established by the Government of the Republic for performance of such work. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja suhtes, kes oli teadlik t&ouml;&ouml;andja niisugusest seisundist, kohaldatakse paragrahvi 130 2. l&otilde;iget. </eesti>
<inglise>Subsection 130 (2) applies in respect of an employee who was aware of such condition of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes ei olnud teadlik t&ouml;&ouml;andja niisugusest seisundist, h&uuml;vitab t&ouml;&ouml;andjale tekitatud kahju t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;iguse normide j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>An employee who was not aware of such condition of the employer shall compensate the employer pursuant to the rules of labour law for damage caused to the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja, kes tekitas kahju seisundis, kus ta ei v&otilde;inud m&otilde;ista oma tegude t&auml;hendust v&otilde;i neid juhtida, ei h&uuml;vita tema poolt tekitatud kahju, v&auml;lja arvatud, kui ta ise viis enda niisugusesse seisundisse alkoholi v&otilde;i narkootiliste v&otilde;i toksiliste ainete tarvitamisega v&otilde;i muul viisil. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employee or employer who causes damage while in such a condition that he or she cannot understand the meaning of or direct his or her actions does not compensate for the damage which he or she caused, except if he or she induced such condition by the use of alcoholic beverages, narcotic drugs, toxic substances or by other means. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 136. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 136. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui leping s&otilde;lmiti pettuse, v&auml;givalla, &auml;hvarduse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja esindaja kuritahtliku kokkuleppe m&otilde;jul t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if contract was entered into with employee under influence of fraud, violence, threat, or malicious agreement with representative of employer </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et leping s&otilde;lmiti pettuse, v&auml;givalla, &auml;hvarduse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja esindaja kuritahtliku kokkuleppe m&otilde;jul t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 8): </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the contract was entered into with the employee under the influence of misrepresentation, violence, threat, or a malicious agreement with a representative of the employer (clause 125 (1) 8)): </inglise>
<eesti>1) kohaldatakse t&ouml;&ouml;taja suhtes, kes oli kannatanuks, paragrahvi 135 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 1. </eesti>
<inglise>1) clause 135 (1) 1) applies to the employee who was the victim. </inglise>
<eesti>Niisugune t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei h&uuml;vita t&ouml;&ouml;andjale tekitatud kahju; </eesti>
<inglise>Such employee shall not compensate for the damage caused to the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kohaldatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja suhtes, kes oli kannatanuks, paragrahvi 130 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 2. </eesti>
<inglise>2) Clause 130 (1) 2) applies in respect of an employer who was a victim. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 137. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 137. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui leping s&otilde;lmiti eksimuse m&otilde;jul </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if contract was entered into under error </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et leping s&otilde;lmiti olulise t&auml;htsusega eksimuse m&otilde;jul (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 9), kohaldatakse paragrahvi 136 punkti 1, kui eksimus tekkis t&ouml;&ouml;andja s&uuml;&uuml;l, ja paragrahvi 130 1. ja 2. l&otilde;iku, kui eksimus tekkis t&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the contract was entered into under an error of essential importance (clause 125 (1) 9)), clause 136 1) applies if the error was caused by the fault of the employer, and subsections 130 (1) and (2) apply if the error was caused by the fault of the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kumbki pool ei olnud eksimuses s&uuml;&uuml;di, on pooltel lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel k&otilde;ik t&ouml;&ouml;lepingust tulenevad &otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise>If neither party was at fault for the error, the parties have all rights arising from the employment contract upon the declaration of invalidity of the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 138. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 138. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja oli piiratult teov&otilde;imeline </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if employer had limited active legal capacity </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et t&ouml;&ouml;andja s&otilde;lmis lepingu alkohoolsete jookide v&otilde;i narkootiliste v&otilde;i toksiliste ainete kuritarvitamise tagaj&auml;rjel piiratult teov&otilde;imeliseks tunnistatud isikuna (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt10), kohaldatakse paragrahvi 130 1. ja 2. l&otilde;iget, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja oli t&ouml;&ouml;andja teov&otilde;ime piiramisest teadlik. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the employer was declared to have limited active legal capacity as a consequence of abuse of alcoholic beverages, narcotic drugs or toxic substances at the time of entry into the contract (clause 125 (1) 10)), subsections 130 (1) and (2) apply if the employee was aware of the limited active legal capacity of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 139. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 139. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel rikuti k&otilde;rgendatud vanusem&auml;&auml;ra </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if higher age limit was violated upon entry into contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel rikuti t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja jaoks kehtestatud k&otilde;rgendatud vanusem&auml;&auml;ra (paragrahvi 125 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 11), kohaldatakse paragrahvi 136 punkti 1. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that higher age limits established for employees or employers were violated upon entry into the contract (clause 125 (1) 11)), clause 136 (1) applies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 140. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 140. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuse tagaj&auml;rjed, kui lepingu s&otilde;lmis t&ouml;&ouml;andja &otilde;igusteta isik </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of invalidity of employment contract if contract was entered into by person without rights of employer </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamisel seet&otilde;ttu, et lepingu s&otilde;lmis juriidilise isiku struktuuri&uuml;ksus, kellele ei ole antud t&ouml;&ouml;andja &otilde;igusi, v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja esindaja, kellel puudub t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimise &otilde;igus (paragrahvi 125 2. l&otilde;ige), kohaldatakse paragrahvi 136 punkti 1. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract on the ground that the contract was entered into by a structural unit of a legal person which does not have employment authority, or by a representative of the employer who lacked the right to enter into employment contracts (subsection 125 (2)), clause 136 (1) applies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 141. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 141. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalisation of declaration of invalidity of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamise kohta teeb t&ouml;&ouml;andja lepingusse kande, milles n&auml;idatakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamise aluse formuleering viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile, t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamise p&auml;ev, t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vituse maksmine ja lepingu j&auml;rgi saadu tagastamine. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer makes an entry regarding the declaration of invalidity of an employment contract in the contract with a statement of the basis for declaration of invalidity of the employment contract and reference to the section, subsection and clause of this Act, the date of declaration of invalidity of the employment contract, payment of compensation to the employee and return of that which was received under the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;leping tunnistati kehtetuks p&auml;rast t&ouml;&ouml;le asumist, vormistatakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu kehtetuks tunnistamine korras, mis on ette n&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise vormistamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>If the employment contract is declared to be invalid after commencement of employment, the declaration of invalidity of the employment contract is formalised pursuant to the procedure prescribed for the formalisation of termination of employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Dispute resolution </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 142. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 142. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste alluvus </eesti>
<inglise>Jurisdiction over disputes </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse kohaldamisel t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja vahel tekkinud vaidlused alluvad kohtule. </eesti>
<inglise>A labour dispute resolution body has jurisdiction over disputes which arise between employees and employers in the application of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 143. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 143. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;vaidlusorganisse p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Period for recourse to dispute resolution body </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse kohaldamisel tekkinud vaidluste lahendamiseks v&otilde;ivad pooled p&ouml;&ouml;rduda t&ouml;&ouml;vaidlusorganisse nelja kuu jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, mis j&auml;rgnes p&auml;evale, mil nad said teada v&otilde;i oleksid pidanud saama teada oma &otilde;iguste rikkumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The parties have recourse to a labour dispute resolution body for resolution of disputes which arise in the application of this Act within four months after the date following the date on which they became aware or should have become aware of the violation of their rights. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise &otilde;igsuse vaidlustamiseks v&otilde;ivad pooled p&ouml;&ouml;rduda t&ouml;&ouml;vaidlusorganisse &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, mis j&auml;rgnes p&auml;evale, mil nad said teada v&otilde;i oleksid pidanud saama teada oma &otilde;iguste rikkumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The parties have recourse to a labour dispute resolution body to dispute the justification for termination of an employment contract within one month, calculated from the date which followed the date that they became aware or should have become aware of the violation of their rights. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 3, 57) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 3, 57) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 144. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 144. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;tegude hindamine kohtus </eesti>
<inglise>Assessment of wrongful acts of employee by labour dispute resolution body </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vaidluse korral t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise &uuml;le paragrahvi 86 punktides 6-8 etten&auml;htud alustel on kohtul &otilde;igus hinnata t&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;teo asjaolusid ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise otstarbekust ning t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le ennistada. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the case of a dispute over the termination of an employment contract on the bases prescribed in clauses 86 6) -8), a labour dispute resolution body has the right to assess the circumstances of the wrongful act of the employee and the purposefulness of termination of the employment contract, and to reinstate the employee in employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le ennistamisel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes mainitud asjaoludel (s&uuml;&uuml;teo v&auml;hene t&auml;htsus jms.) ei ole t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igust h&uuml;vitusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon reinstatement of an employee in employment in the circumstances referred to in subsection (1) of this section (minor importance of the wrongful act, etc.), the employee does not have the right to compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>(31.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 311) </eesti>
<inglise>(31.05.2001 entered into force 30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 311) </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(31.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 311) </eesti>
<inglise>(31.05.2001 entered into force 30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 311) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 145. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 145. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide t&auml;itmise &uuml;le teostab T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State supervision over compliance with this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof shall be exercised by the Labour Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajal ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektoril on &otilde;igus teha ettekirjutusi k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide rikkumise korral ning kontrollida ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of violation of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof, heads of regional offices of the Labour Inspectorate and labour inspectors of the location (residence) of employers have the right to issue precepts and inspect compliance with the precepts. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja ja t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutused on t&ouml;&ouml;andjale t&auml;itmiseks kohustuslikud. </eesti>
<inglise>Precepts issued by heads of regional offices of the Labour Inspectorates and labour inspectors are mandatory for employers. </inglise>
<eesti>(31.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 311) </eesti>
<inglise>(31.05.2001 entered into force 30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 311) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 146. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 146. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettekirjutuse vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Contestation of precept </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja ei n&otilde;ustu oma asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutusega, on tal &otilde;igus esitada kas T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajale v&otilde;i halduskohtule kaebus ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evast arvates k&uuml;mne kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an employer does not agree with a precept issued by a labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer, the employer has the right to file a complaint with the head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate or with an administrative court within ten calendar days after date of receipt of the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ettekirjutuse on teinud T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja, on t&ouml;&ouml;andjal ettekirjutusega mitten&otilde;ustumise korral &otilde;igus esitada kaebus kas T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni peadirektorile v&otilde;i halduskohtule ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evast arvates k&uuml;mne kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>If an employer does not agree with a precept issued by a head of a regional office of the Labour Inspectorate, the employer has the right to file a complaint with the Director General of the Labour Inspectorate or with an administrative court within ten calendar days after date of receipt of the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaebuse esitamine ei vabasta kohustusest ettekirjutust t&auml;ita. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The filing of a complaint shall not discharge the person from the obligation to comply with the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajal, T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni peadirektoril v&otilde;i halduskohtul on &otilde;igus kaebuse esitaja taotlusel v&otilde;i oma algatusel peatada ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmine kuni kaebuse lahendamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Heads of regional offices of the Labour Inspectorate, the Director General of the Labour Inspectorate and administrative courts have the right to suspend, on application of a complainant or at their own discretion, the enforcement of a precept until the settlement of a complaint. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja v&otilde;i T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni peadirektor vaatab kaebuse l&auml;bi ning kaebuse saamise p&auml;evast arvates &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul otsustab, kas j&auml;tta ettekirjutus j&otilde;usse, see muuta v&otilde;i t&uuml;histada. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate or the Director General of the Labour Inspectorate shall review the complaint and make a decision, within one week after the date of receipt of the complaint, on whether the precept remains in force, is amended or revoked. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus tehakse kaebuse esitajale teatavaks allkirja vastu v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel v&auml;ljastusteatega. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall be communicated to the complainant against a signature or sent by post with advice of delivery. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kaebuse esitaja T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja v&otilde;i T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni peadirektori otsusega ei n&otilde;ustu, v&otilde;ib ta selle vaidlustada halduskohtus. </eesti>
<inglise>If the complainant does not agree with the decision of the head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate or the Director General of the Labour Inspectorate the complainant may appeal it in an administrative court. </inglise>
